[LL_WEBREPORT_CALL NAME:<script name> PARM:<arg1>:<arg2>:<argN> /]
Calls a server side Oscript function defined by LL_WEBREPORT_STARTSCRIPT and LL_WEBREPORT_ENDSCRIPT tags. The particular script to call is identified by the <script name> parameter. The script may optionally be passed a list of arguments seperated by semi-colons.

Note that server side scripting must be enabled by an Administrator at the server level and for each WebReport each time a new reportview is added. Scripts are rendered inactive unless enabled.

Server side scripting is powerful but must be used with great care. Users should read all the related documentation before using server side scripting. See Server Side Scripting for a summary and refer to the PDF format WebReports User Guide available on the Knowledge Center which contains comprehensive documentation and examples.

		
[LL_WEBREPORT_COMPILER RUNTIMETAGS:<true/false> /]
Determines if constants and parameters in the report should be evaluated at runtime for tags. This is required if any tags are defined in the constants tab. It is effectively the same as having an EVAL sub-tag on each parameter and constant.

For example, having [LL_REPTAG_&p /] in a report with &p=[LL_REPTAG_"literal" UPPER /] in the URL will output:

[LL_REPTAG_"literal" UPPER /].
By enabling RUNTIMETAGS with [LL_WEBREPORT_COMPILER RUNTIMETAGS:TRUE /] this would be evaluated to:

LITERAL.
See also: EVAL   

		
[LL_WEBREPORT_COMPRESS /]
This tag removes white space from the final output. All carriage returns, line breaks, tabs, and multiple spaces are replaced with a single space. Care must be taken if a page contains improperly formatted Javascript. If use of this tag causes Javascript errors, then consider removing the tag or fixing the Javascript in the page.

This tag operates only on the content, and has no effect on the rest of the page.

		
[LL_WEBREPORT_ENABLEROWFILTERS /]
Enables support for filtering rows in the data source dynamically using the "fc_filters" request parameter. This parameter has to be in JSON format represented as an array of objects. Each object must have valid "column", "operator" and "value" properties. Any invalid filters will be ignored.

The evaulation of these filters is the same as the [LL_WEBREPORT_IF /] and [LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDEIF /] tags. All string evaluations are case-insensitive. See the Advanced Notes on Logical Expressions section of the Online User Help for more detailed information.

Filtering using this mechanism will be reflected in the [LL_REPTAG_FILTEREDROWS /] tag and can be used with WebReport pagination using [LL_REPTAG_INCLUDERANGE /].


Usage Examples:

[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"==", "value":"Contract"}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column equals "Contract".
[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"!=", "value":"Contract"}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column is NOT equal to "Contract".
[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"==", "value":"Contract"},{ "column":"Status" , "operator":"==", "value":"Final"}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column equals "Contract" AND the value in the Status column equals "Final".
[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"IN", "value":["SOP","Contract"]}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column equals "SOP" OR "Contract".
[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"NOTIN", "value":["SOP","Contract"]}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column is NOT equal to "SOP" OR "Contract".
[{ "column":"Version" , "operator":"<", "value":5}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the Version column is less than 5.
[{ "column":"Version" , "operator":"<=", "value":5}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the Version column is less than or equal to 5.
[{ "column":"Version" , "operator":">", "value":5}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the Version column is greater than 5.
[{ "column":"Version" , "operator":">=", "value":5}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the Version column is greater than or equal to 5.
[{ "column":"DocType" , "operator":"CONTAINS", "value":"Con"}]
This will return all rows in the data source where the value in the DocType column contains the string "Con".
See also: LL_REPTAG_FILTEREDROWS   LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDEIF   LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDERANGE   

		
