Data Tag Name	Description	H	R	F
[LL_REPTAG=<column name> /]
Causes WebReports to insert the source data specified by the <columnname> into the output report. The tag should only be used in the row section of a WebReport unless it is being used as an argument for the LL_WEBREPORT_INSERTJSON tag. The optional list of sub-tags is used to specify formatting options. These sub-tags should be separated by spaces. See the sub-tag definition table for information on these tags.

The use of single or double quotes to delimit a column name is supported. Using quotes is only mandatory for referencing data source column names that contain a space character. This also applies if the LiveReport renames a column to a name containing a space character. Double quotes should not be used if the LL_REPTAG is inside a conditional tag. Examples:

[LL_REPTAG=NAME /]
[LL_REPTAG="NAME" /]
[LL_REPTAG="FIRST NAME" /]
[LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDEIF "John" != "[LL_REPTAG='FIRST NAME' /]" /]
		
[LL_REPTAG_! /]
This tag is a shortcut to [LL_REPTAG_%<variablename> CURRENTVAL /].

For example, the following two tags are equal:

[LL_REPTAG_%myVar CURRENTVAL /]
[LL_REPTAG_!myVar /]
See also: ADDVAR   CONCATVAR   CURRENTVAL   

		
[LL_REPTAG_$ /]
This tag provides a way to access constants that have been defined using the Properties->Constants tab. The constant name in the Reportview should exactly match the name that has been specified on the constants page. The tag is replaced by the value that has been defined for the corresponding constant. E.g. If a constant called MyConst has been defined with a constant value of '12345', the following tag would return '12345':

[LL_REPTAG_$MyConst /]
Constants are particularly useful for referencing Sub-Webreports and other Content Server objects as it means that objectids don't need to be hardcoded within the Reportview. Also, when using XML to export WebReports applications, constants allow the objects to be 'relinked' on XML import to the new system. More information on constants can be found on the Constant Usage page.

		
[LL_REPTAG_% /]
This tag provides a way to reference variables that have been defined by using SETVAR, ADDVAR or CONCATVAR. If, for example, ADDVAR had been used in the row section to accumulate a mathematical total in a variable called MyVar, the final total could be accessed by using:

[LL_REPTAG_%MyVar /]
Note: [LL_REPTAG_%MyVar /] syntax should only be used to return the final value of a variable in the report's output. This value is substituted in at the end of report execution when the final value is known. This means that using sub-tags, or any other runtime actions, are not supported with this type of variable syntax. To use sub-tags with a variable value please use [LL_REPTAG_!MyVar /] or CURRENTVAL to ensure the current variable value is passed into the sub-tag for processing.

More information on using variable tags and the associated sub-tags can be found in the Advanced Information section: Variables & Variable Action Sub-tags.

See also: ADDVAR   CONCATVAR   CURRENTVAL   

		
[LL_REPTAG_& /]
This tag provides a means of accessing any parameter in the URL used to invoke the WebReport. Any values in the URL prefixed by an ampersand (&) can be referenced in this way. This means that existing parameters such as &ObjAction can be referenced as well as any number of bespoke parameters. For example, if the following URL was executed:

...?func=ll&objId=47478&objAction=RunReport&myparm=testdata&nexturl=....
The parameter, myparm, can be accessed by using: [LL_REPTAG_&myparm /]. This tag will resolve to the value in the URL (testdata in this example) where it can be used as output or as part of a conditional statement e.g.

[LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDEIF "[LL_REPTAG_&myparm /]" == "testdata" /]
If a parameter is referenced in the Reportview but is not provided in the URL a blank string will be inserted in the output unless a parameter default is set on the Properties->Parameters page. See Using Parameters for more information.

		
[LL_REPTAG_<column number> /]
Reference column data with the column number. Content Server columns are numbered from left to right starting at 1. Note the use of an "_" underscore instead of an "=" equal sign in this form of LL_REPTAG (this roughly matches the Content Server WebForm tag model). This form of the tag can be useful if one reportview is to be used in multiple WebReports where the column titles may vary.

		
[LL_REPTAG_<literal text> /]
This tag provides a means of specifying a string of text to be inserted in the Reportview. Any sub-tags included in this tag definition will operate on the text specified between the two quotes. Either double quotes or single quotes may be used but must be matched.

[LL_REPTAG_"this text will be displayed in capitals" UPPER /]
		
[LL_REPTAG_@<function><reference options> /]
This tag type provides data functions. The result of each function is inserted into the output; however, these tags are currently only supported in the header or footer of a Reportview (i.e. before the [LL_WEBREPORT_STARTROW /] or after the [LL_WEBREPORT_ENDROW /] tag).

For each function there are optional characters following the function name which reference either a specific row of data or a column or both. These reference characters are:

[r] This optional parameter (only used by @DATA) specifies the row index (note, the reserved word LAST can be used instead of r)
and can be followed by:

_c specifies a column number, or
_<colname> specifies a column name
When one of the functions below is specified, the function will be executed against which ever data has been referenced. For any math tags, if non-numeric values are found in the column then an error is returned. Note that there are sub-tags which will help to format the values returned by these functions.

Examples:

If the average of column 2 is required the following syntax could be used:

[LL_REPTAG_@AVERAGE_2 /]
If the sum of a column called "hours" is required, the following syntax could be used:

[LL_REPTAG_@SUM_hours /]
If the contents of a column called dataid from the last row of data is required, the following syntax could be used:

[LL_REPTAG_@DATA[last]_dataid /]
If the contents of a column 2 from row 1 of the data is required, the following syntax could be used:

[LL_REPTAG_@DATA[ 1 ]_2 /]
If the contents of a field in the Content Server request response is required, the following syntax could be used:

[LL_REPTAG_@RESPONSEDATA.HASSTAGEDCONTENT /]
[LL_REPTAG_@AVERAGE_<column> /]	Returns the average of all valid numbers in the specified column.
[LL_REPTAG_@DATA[r]_<column> /]	Returns a single cell of data specified by the row and column.
[LL_REPTAG_@MIN_<column> /]	Returns the lowest (minimum) value from all the values in the specified column.
[LL_REPTAG_@MAX_<column> /]	Returns the greatest (maximum) value from all the values in the specified column.
[LL_REPTAG_@RESPONSEDATA.<data field name> /]	Returns fields returned by Content Server in the response to a request. These fields are normally used in Content Server pages to display data. For example, some Content Server browse pages use a field in the response from a browse request called: response.data.hasStagedContent. This value could be referenced in a WebReport using: [LL_REPTAG_@RESPONSEDATA.hasStagedContent /].
[LL_REPTAG_@SUM_<column> /]	Returns the sum of all the values in the specified column.
		
[LL_REPTAG_ACTUALROWS /]
This tag returns the number of rows included in the WebReport by the INCLUDEIF tag. This differs from the total number of rows provided by the data source. For example, if the WebReport is executed in conjunction with a data source returning ten rows of data, but the INCLUDEIF restricts the output to three rows then TOTALROWS = 10 and ACTUALROWS = 3. This feature is only supported in the header and footer sections of the WebReport.

See also: LL_REPTAG_FILTEREDROWS   LL_REPTAG_TOTALROWS   LL_REPTAG_TOTALSOURCEROWS   

		
[LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID /]
This tag returns the user ID of the user that ran the WebReport, regardless of whether the RunAs feature is set.

For example, if User 1 runs a WebReport that has RunAs set to User 2, the [LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID /] tag will return the ID of User 1 whereas the [LL_REPTAG_USERID /] tag will return the ID of User 2.

		
[LL_REPTAG_APPSUPPORTDIR /]
Provides the correct path to reference the support directory used by Content Server Applications Management.

		
[LL_REPTAG_BUSINESSWORKSPACESVOLUMEID /]
Returns the DataID of the Business Workspaces volume.

		
[LL_REPTAG_CATEGORIESVOLUMEID /]
Returns the DataID of the Categories volume.

		
[LL_REPTAG_CLASSIFICATIONSVOLUMEID /]
