The origin http header consists of any parameters passed into the Smart View URL as part of a request. These parameters are only accessible in Smart View WebReport widgets, and can be further manipulated by any ASSOC subtag, for example:

If your request contains the following:

OriginParams: ?originParam1=salesforce&originParam2=Account&originParam3=2019&originParm4=1.5

You may extract it for further processing by leveraging the tag like so:

[LL_REPTAG_ORIGINPARAMS ASSOC:"originParam1" /]
Which will return the parameter keyed to "originParam1", returning the string, "salesforce"

