[LL_REPTAG_ORIGROWNUM /]
Returns the data source row number after any WebReports sorting has occurred, but before any WebReports filtering has occurred. This tag differs from the [LL_REPTAG_ROWNUM /] tag in that it will always return the original row number from the data source regardless of how many rows are actually returned by the WebReport. It is useful for [LL_REPTAG_INCLUDEIF /] conditions that need to react to a row number as the normal [LL_REPTAG_ROWNUM /] tag can't be used in an [LL_WEBREPORT_INCLUDEIF /] statement. This tag is similar to the [LL_REPTAG_SOURCEROWNUM /] tag; however, it differs from the [LL_REPTAG_SOURCEROWNUM /] tag in that it reflects the order of rows after any WebReport SORT tags have been processed whereas [LL_REPTAG_SOURCEROWNUM /] reflects the order of rows before any WebReports SORT tags have been processed.

See also: LL_REPTAG_ROWNUM   LL_REPTAG_SOURCEROWNUM   

		
[LL_REPTAG_OTCSTICKET /]
This tag generates an OTCSTicket from the current user's cookie. This is the same ticket which is returned when calling a POST against the /auth resource in the Content Server REST API. This can then be added as an HTTP request header to make Content Server REST API requests. The header should be in the format OTCSTicket: <ticketValue>.

IMPORTANT: If you are setting the value as a javascript variable, please ensure you only ever use this as a local variable and never as a global. Setting this value as a global variable could compromise the security of your system.

An example of using this ticket to make a call to execute a Content Server search via the Rest API is:

			
	<script>
		var data = {
				where: "test"
			  };
		$.ajax({
			  url: "[LL_REPTAG_URLPREFIX /]/api/v2/search",
			  beforeSend: function(xhr){xhr.setRequestHeader('OTCSTicket', [LL_REPTAG_OTCSTICKET QUOTE /]);},
			  method: "POST",
			  data: data,
			  success: function (response){
				console.log(response);
			  },
			  error: function (error){
				console.log(error);
			  }
		});
	</script>
	
		
