[LL_REPTAG_TRIGGERCATEGORYVALUECHANGES /]
Returns a RecArray containing the old and new values of category attributes when a category update event occurs.

The RecArray will contain the following columns:

CATID: The ID of the category that was updated.
ATTRID: The ID of the attribute that was updated.
OLDVALUE: The value of the attribute prior to the update. Will return ? (undefined) if the no value was present (for example if a new row was added).
NEWVALUE: The new value of the attribute after the update.
SETNAME: The name of the set, if the attribute is contained in a set. Will return ? (undefined) otherwise.
SETINDEX: The set index, if the attribute is contained in a set. Will return ? (undefined) otherwise.
ATTRINDEX: The index of the attribute. Will always return a value. The index will be 1 if the attribute is not a multi-value attribute.

See also: RECARRAY   RECORD   

		
