Sub-Tag Reference Guide

These sub-tags are used to provide formatting or additional functions with any of the REPTAG-type tags (i.e. not content control tags),
for example, [LL_REPTAG_1 UPPER /] or [LL_REPTAG=colname LOWER /].
They can be chained with other sub-tags, for example, [LL_REPTAG_1 NODEINFO:PARENTID PERMINFO:OWNER /].	Section
Sub-Tag Name	Description	H	R	F
A2UTF8
Converts an ASCII string to a UTF-8 string.

		
ABS
Displays the absolute value of a number.

See also: ADD   DIVIDE   MULTIPLY   MODULUS   SUBTRACT   TIMESINCE   

		
ADD
Adds a value to the main tag. The exact operation depends on the types.

The return value of the following expression will depend on the types.

[LL_REPTAG_'X' ADD:Y /]
Type of X	Type of Y	Returns	Example
Integer or Real	Integer or Real	X + Y	[LL_REPTAG_'5' ADD:2.2 /]

returns 7.2
Date	Integer (seconds)	X + Y	[LL_REPTAG_'May 1 2011' ADD:86400 /]

returns Mon May 02 00:00:00 2011
List	List	{ @X,@Y}	[LL_REPTAG_'{1,2,3}' ADD:'{4,5,6}' /]

returns {1,2,3,4,5,6}
List	any type	{ @X,Y}	[LL_REPTAG_'{1,2,3}' ADD:'four' /]

returns {1,2,3,'four'}
Assoc	Assoc	Merges X & Y. Y takes precedence on duplicate keys.	[LL_REPTAG_"A<?,1,'key1'=1>" ADD:"A<?,1,'key1'=2,'key2'=5>" /]

returns A<1,1,'key1'=2,'key2'=5>
Record	Record	Merges X & Y. Y takes precedence on duplicate keys. Column order is lost.	[LL_REPTAG_"R<'key1'=1>" ADD:"R<'key1'=2,'key2'=5>" /]

returns R<'key1'=2,'key2'=5>
RecArray	RecArray	Appends Y to X, as long as X & Y have the same fields.	[LL_REPTAG_"V{<'fruit','color'><'banana','yellow'>}" ADD:"V{<'fruit','color'><'orange','orange'>}" /]

returns V{<'fruit','color'><'banana','yellow'><'orange','orange'>}
anything else	anything else	String(X) + String(Y)	[LL_REPTAG_"abc" ADD:"3" /]

returns abc3
See also: DIVIDE   MULTIPLY   MODULUS   SUBTRACT   TIMESINCE   

		
ADDVAR:<variable name>
Adds the value of the tag (after formatting by any previous sub-tags) with the current contents of a variable which can later be referenced using the specified variable name. This tag only works when numeric values are returned by a tag. The first time this sub-tag is used, it behaves as if the variable already existed with the value of zero(0). E.g.

[LL_REPTAG=COST ADDVAR:subtotal /]
In this example if the values 26, 34, and 14 were returned as values from the tag "cost" then , the variable tag: [LL_REPTAG_%subtotal /] would return: 74

More information on using ADDVAR, variable tags and other sub-tags associated with managing variables can be found in the Advanced Information section: Variables & Variable Action Sub-tags.

See also: SETVAR   CONCATVAR   CURRENTVAL   

		
APPPROPERTY:<property name>
Returns a string from the application's properties file for user's default metadata language.
If a properties file does not exist for the user's default metadata language then the string will be returned from the application's properties file for the system default language.
If a properties file does not exist for the system default language then the string will be returned from the application's en_US properties file.
If the property is not found in the properties file, or the application has no properties files then an error message will be returned.

Expects an application name in the main tag.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_"myapplication" APPPROPERTY:"MYAPPLICATION_LABEL.Instructions" /]
will return the value of the MYAPPLICATION_LABEL.Instructions string from the myapplication_language.properties file for the application.

		
ASSOC:<key>
or
ASSOC:[index]
Returns the value of the key field if the returned data type is a Content Server ASSOC. Either the key itself or an integer representing the key location within the ASSOC can be used. Note: this sub-tag can be used repetitively where an ASSOC may be nested.

See also: ASSOCACTION   LIST   RECORD   RECARRAY   

		
ASSOCACTION
This sub-tag allows the creation and manipulation of data in a Content Server Assoc data type. Use the SETVAR sub-tag to store the Assoc to allow it to be accessed by subsequent tags.

Action	Operation	Description
ADD	ASSOCACTION:ADD:<Key>:<Value>	Adds a key/value pair to the Assoc defined in the main tag, and returns the updated Assoc.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_!myAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"Name":"Bob" SETVAR:myAssoc /] will add the key "Name" with the value "Bob" to the Assoc defined in the myAssoc variable, then save the updated Assoc back to the myAssoc variable.
CHANGE	ASSOCACTION:CHANGE:<Key>:<Value>	Changes the value of a key in the Assoc defined in the main tag, and returns the updated Assoc.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_!myAssoc ASSOCACTION:CHANGE:"Name":"Fred" SETVAR:myAssoc /] will change the value of the "Name" key to "Fred" in the Assoc defined in the myAssoc variable, then save the updated Assoc back to the myAssoc variable.
CREATE	ASSOCACTION:CREATE	Creates an Assoc. If the main tag is empty string, then an empty Assoc will be created. If the main tag contains a list of key/value pairs then the data will be used to populate the Assoc. Returns the resultant Assoc.

Examples:

[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:myAssoc /] will create an empty Assoc and save it to the myAssoc variable.

[LL_REPTAG_'{ { "Name", "Bob" }, { "Fruit", "Apple" } }' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:myAssoc /] will create an Assoc and populate it with the keys "Name" and "Fruit" with the values "Bob" and "Apple" respectively, then save it to the myAssoc variable.
DELETE	ASSOCACTION:DELETE:<Key>	Deletes a key from the Assoc defined in the main tag, and returns the updated Assoc.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_!myAssoc ASSOCACTION:DELETE:"Fruit" SETVAR:myAssoc /] will delete the key "Fruit" from the Assoc defined in the myAssoc variable, then save the updated Assoc back to the myAssoc variable.
FROMRECORD	ASSOCACTION:FROMRECORD	Returns an Assoc created from the Record defined in the main tag.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE RECARRAY:1 ASSOCACTION:FROMRECORD SETVAR:myAssoc /] will create an Assoc from the first row of the data source, then save it to the myAssoc variable.
MERGE	ASSOCACTION:MERGE:<Assoc to be merged into the Assoc defined in the main tag>	Merges the Assoc supplied as an argument with the Assoc defined in the main tag, and returns the updated Assoc.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_!myAssoc ASSOCACTION:MERGE:[LL_REPTAG_!myOtherAssoc /] SETVAR:myAssoc /] will merge the data from the Assoc defined in the myOtherAssoc variable with the data in the Assoc defined in the myAssoc variable, then save the resultant Assoc back to the myAssoc variable.
TORECORD	ASSOCACTION:TORECORD	Returns a Record created from the Assoc defined in the main tag.

Example:

[LL_REPTAG_!myAssoc ASSOCACTION:TORECORD SETVAR:myRecord /] will create a Record from the Assoc defined in the myAssoc variable, then save it to the myRecord variable.
See also: ASSOC   SETVAR   

		
AUDITACTION:<operation>
Expects a valid Content Server ID in the main tag (either a user/group ID or a DataID for a Content Server node), and performs an action to generate an audit event. This will result in a new row added to the DAuditNew database view and optional rows to the DAuditMore view.

Use AUDITACTION:USER to specify that the audit action is for a user/group ID, or AUDITACTION:NODE for a node. If neither of the :USER or :NODE arguments are provided, then if the specified ID is a valid user/group ID, the UserID field of the DAuditNew record will be set, otherwise if the ID is a valid node ID, the DataID field will be set instead. Whichever of UserID or DataID that is not used will be set to NULL.
The PerformerID field for the new audit record will always be set to the ID for whichever user context was active when the sub-tag is executed. This happens even if the "Run As" feature has been used to run the WebReport in a different user context. In this case, a row will be added to the DAuditMore view (linked using the eventID key) that shows the ID of the selected "Run As" user.

In addition to the UserID, DataID and PerformerID columns, values can be specified for several other fields as specified in table below.

Append the SHOW sub-tag to return the eventID of the audit event.

Note that the WebReports Custom Audit Event checkbox must be ticked on the Set Auditing Interests administration page in order for the AUDITACTION sub-tag to work.

Format	Description
AUDITACTION:[USER or NODE]:<value>	Adds an entry to the DAuditNew view with the value specified set to the 'Value1' column.
AUDITACTION:[USER or NODE]:<fixed key>:<value>:<fixed key>:<value>...	Adds an entry to the DAuditNew view with multiple values set to any of the fixed keys (column names in DAuditNew), which can be one of 'Value1', 'Value2' or 'ValueKey'.
AUDITACTION:[USER or NODE]:<KeyStr>:<ValueStr>:<KeyStr>:<ValueStr>...	Adds key-value pairs into the DAuditMore view. Any value(s) specified in <KeyStr> will be added to the 'KeyStr' column, while any value(s) specified in <ValueStr> will be added to the 'ValueStr' column.
See also: SHOW   

		
AUDITINFO:<operation>
Expects a valid Content Server Node ID and returns details from the most recent Audit Event for the object, and allows you to specify which column from DAuditNew to display.

Previously fetched audit details are cached per node ID. If the audit is modified outside of the context of a WebReport, you may append an optional :NOCACHE parameter to AUDITINFO or AUDITINFO:<option> to ensure a fresh fetch from the database.

It supports custom audit entries generated by the AUDITACTION sub-tag, as well as the RunAs feature.

Format	Description
AUDITINFO:ACTUALUSER	For 'WebReports Run' events, if the WebReport was executed by the RunAs feature, the ID of the RunAs user will be displayed.
AUDITINFO:AUDITDATE	Returns the AuditDate value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:AUDITID	Returns the AuditID value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:AUDITSTR	Returns the AuditStr value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:EVENTID	Returns the EventID value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:KEYSTR:<key>	This option looks up the "key" value in the KeyStr column of DAuditMore, and returns the corresponding value of the ValueStr column. Useful to return the value of ValueStr for a specific custom value.
AUDITINFO:PERFORMERID	Returns the PerformerID value of the event from the DAuditNew table. For 'WebReports Run' events, use the :ACTUALUSER option to display the ID of the RunAs user.
AUDITINFO:SUBTYPE	Returns the SubType value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:USERID	Returns the UserID value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:VALUE1	Returns the Value1 value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:VALUE2	Returns the Value2 value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
AUDITINFO:VALUEKEY	Returns the ValueKey value of the event from the DAuditNew table.
