CAT:<parm>
Returns information about the Categories and Attributes associated with the current object ID. This sub-tag supports both attribute sets and multi-value attributes through use of the MV and SET operators.

For example: [LL_REPTAG=DATAID CAT:<category>:<attribute>:DISPLAY /] will return the attribute value stored in the category whose display name or ID matches the <category> value and the attribute whose display name or ID matches the <attribute> value for any attribute type. If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute or an attribute set then a comma-separated list of values will be returned.

If using a WebReport to update category values using the CATACTION sub-tag with the NOCOMMIT argument, you can retrieve the uncommitted category values from the cache by appending the argument :FROMCACHE to your CAT syntax.

For example,

[LL_REPTAG=DATAID CATACTION:SETVALUE:<catname>:<attname>:<new value>:NOCOMMIT /]
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID CAT:<catname>:<attname>:DISPLAY /] will display the original value of the attribute, as the CATACTION change hasn't been committed yet.
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID CAT:<catname>:<attname>:DISPLAY:FROMCACHE /] will display the new value of the attribute from the cache.
To return Category data for a specific version of a node see the VERSIONCAT sub-tag.

Syntax	Description
CAT	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on the presence of one or more categories assigned to the node.
CAT:JSARRAY	This is a unique option for the CAT sub-tag which results in a JavaScript object representation of all the category and attribute data (including full support for sets and multi-values) for a specific node. For detailed information on this feature see the Category JSARRAY advanced help.
CAT:RAW	This option results in a flat oscript representation of all the category and attribute data associated with a specific node.

See the Request as Data Source advanced help for how to use the output of this, and related tags, as the data source to another WebReport.

See the TOJSON sub-tag for how to convert this into a data structure that can be interpreted by JavaScript in the client.

See related tags LLURL:FUNCTIONMENU:RAW and LLURL:ADDITEM:ITEMMENU:RAW.
CAT:DISPLAY	Will return a string containing a list of semi-colon separated category names assigned to the node. Any category containing mandatory attributes will be suffixed with an exclamation in square brackets - [!].
CAT:MAND	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether a category containing a mandatory attribute is assigned to the node.
CAT:<category>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on the presence of the <category> category.
CAT:<category>:DISPLAY	Will return a string containing a list of semi-colon separated attribute values for the category specified in <category>. If either attribute sets or multi-value attributes are contained in the category they will be displayed in the following syntax:
'attval1;attval2;[SET3:attval4,attval5,[MV6:attval7,attval8]];attval9'
Here attval1, attval2 & attval9 are regular attribute values. [SET3: represents the start of an attribute set where 3 is the attribute ID of the set (see note). Contained in the attribute set are two regular attributes (attval4 & attval5) and a multi-value attribute, starting [MV6:, with 6 being the attribute ID of the multi-value attribute. The multi-value attribute contains two values for attribute 6, these are: attval7 & attval8.

N.B: Attribute IDs can be identified by looking at the browser status bar whilst hovering over the attribute name in the category definition page.
