CAT:<category>:INHERITABLE	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether the category is inheritable or not.
CAT:<category>:LIST	Will return a list containing all of the attribute values for the category specified in <category>. If either attribute sets or multi-value attributes are contained in the category then they will be displayed in the following syntax:
'attval1;attval2;[SET3:attval4,attval5,[MV6:attval7,attval8]];attval9'
Here attval1, attval2 & attval9 are regular attribute values. [SET3: represents the start of an attribute set where 3 is the attribute ID of the set (see note). Contained in the attribute set are two regular attributes (attval4 & attval5) and a multi-value attribute, starting [MV6:, with 6 being the attribute ID of the multi-value attribute. The multi-value attribute contains two values for attribute 6, these are: attval7 & attval8.

Note that attribute IDs can be identified by looking at the browser status bar whilst hovering over the attribute name in the category definition page.
CAT:<category>:UPGRADEABLE	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether the category is upgradeable or not.
CAT:<category>:VERSION	Will return the version number of <category> if the category is present.
CAT:<category>:<attribute>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a non-blank value in the category, <category>. If an attribute set is specified in <attribute>, a single entry in any one of the set's attribute values will cause this to return TRUE.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, a single entry in any one will also cause this to return TRUE.  <attribute> can also be nested within an attribute set either as a regular attribute or a multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category>. If <attribute> is an attribute set or a multi-value attribute a comma-separated list of values will be returned.
CAT:<category>:<attribute>:ID	Will return the ID of the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> if it is present. If <attribute> exists inside an attribute set, it will be returned if no attribute matching <attribute> exists at the top level in the category.  If <attribute> exists at the top level of the category and within an attribute set of the same category, the attribute ID at the top level (not within the set) will take precedence.
CAT:<category>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a value equal to <attval> in the category, <category>.  <attribute> may be an attribute within an attribute set (including a multi-value), or any element within a multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT
Will return the number of multi-value attributes in use.
CAT:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>
Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of a specific non-blank element in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.  If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
CAT:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:<attval>
Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of <attval> in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>,  for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
CAT:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> at the index location <n> where <n> is a positive integer between 1 and n.  The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
CAT:<category>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.  For example, if <attval> exists in the third element of <attribute>, the number 3 will be returned.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>	Uses the SET operator allowing attribute sets to be explicitly referenced.  This example will return TRUE if attribute, <attribute> within set, <set> is non-blank.  Only attributes within <set> can be referenced so if <attribute> exists outside the set, it will not be found.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, TRUE will be returned if any field within it is non-blank.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category>, if <attribute> is an attribute within <set>.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, a comma-separated list of the defined values will be returned.  If no defined value exists, either in a multi-value attribute, or a standard attribute, an empty list will be returned.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:ID	Will return the ID of the attribute <attribute> within the set <set>.  If <attribute> exists outside <set> it will not be returned.  <attribute> can be either a regular or multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a value equal to <attval> in the set, <set>.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, all elements will be checked for equality against <attval>, if any match, TRUE will be returned.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT	Will return number of multi-value attributes that have been populated.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>	Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of a specific non-blank element in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of <attval> in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n> where <n> is a positive integer between 1 and n.  The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
CAT:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:ATTRIBUTE:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value set, <set>, for the category, <category> and attribute, <attribute>, containing a value equal to the value specified in <attval>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:COUNT	Returns the number of rows in the multi-value set.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, has a non-blank attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will display the value of an attribute <attribute> within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:ID	Will display the ID of an attribute <attribute> within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, has a attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <n>, within the category, <category> that is equal to the value specified in <attval>. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT	Returns the number of multi-value attributes in use in the multi-value set.
