CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:<m>:DISPLAY	Will display the value of an multi-value attribute <attribute>, at the index location <m>, within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:<m>:<attval>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, at the index location <n>, has a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <m> whose value is equal to the value specified in <attval>.
CAT:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a multi-value set, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.
