CHECKURL
or
CHECKURL:<defaultURL>
Checks a URL for potential cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks, and returns either an empty string or the default URL provided if potential XSS syntax is found.

For example:

[LL_REPTAG_NEXTURL CHECKURL /]
If the passed nextURL value contains a potential XSS attack, the CHECKURL sub-tag resolves to an empty string.

CHECKURL also accepts a parameter that can be used to define a default URL if an XSS attack is detected, for example:

[LL_REPTAG_'?func=ll&objId=<IDofWebReport>&objAction=RunReport&nexturl="><script>alert(1)</script>' CHECKURL:[LL_REPTAG_MYID LLURL:REPORT /] /]
This will resolve to the value of [LL_REPTAG_MYID LLURL:REPORT /] because CHECKURL detected potential XSS syntax in the data tag.

See also: LL_REPTAG_NEXTURL   ESCAPEURL   

		
