Converts characters such as less than or greater than to HTML escape syntax. For example: If [LL_REPTAG_1 /] normally returns <hello>, [LL_REPTAG_1 ESCAPEHTML /] will return: <Hello>.

		
ESCAPEJSON
Converts a specified string to an escaped JSON format. For example: If [LL_REPTAG_1 /] normally returns quote"quote, [LL_REPTAG_1 ESCAPEJSON /] will return: quote\u0022quote. For more information on JSON escape characters see http://www.json.org.

		
ESCAPESTR
Converts characters such as line feeds, carriage returns and quotes to the standard C language syntax e.g. \r for carriage returns. This sub-tag is essential for any script variable assignments as carriage returns and other characters like quotes will cause an error. For example: Rows[x] = "[LL_REPTAG_1 ESCAPESTR /]";

		
ESCAPEURL
Converts non-alphanumeric characters into URL hexadecimal sequences.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_"http://www.bogus.com/somefile" ESCAPEURL /] will return "http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Ebogus%2Ecom%2Fsomefile".

		
ESCAPEWR
Prevents any WebReport's tag syntax that may be included in the data from being interpreted as valid tag syntax.

		
ESCAPEXML
Converts data to XML compatible format by escaping special characters, such as greater-than, less-than, ampersand and apostrophe.

		
EVAL
Processes any Webreport tags found in the main tag. For example,

[LL_REPTAG_&p /] // with &p=[LL_REPTAG_'uppercase' UPPER /],
will return "[LL_REPTAG_'uppercase' UPPER /]". Adding the EVAL sub-tag will evaluate any sub-tags found in the data. That is,

[LL_REPTAG_&p EVAL /] // with &p=[LL_REPTAG_'uppercase' UPPER /],
will return "UPPERCASE".
		
EVEN
Returns true if the data returned by the main tag is an even number. Returns false otherwise. This can be used with a ROWNUM tag to create code that can alternate from row to row (e.g. row colour). Example:

[LL_WEBREPORT_IF "TRUE" == "[LL_REPTAG_ROWNUM ODD /]" /]
   <tr class="oddrow">
[LL_WEBREPORT_ENDIF /]

[LL_WEBREPORT_IF "TRUE" == "[LL_REPTAG_ROWNUM EVEN /]" /]
   <tr class="evenrow">
[LL_WEBREPORT_ENDIF /]
		
EXCLUDE:<condition>
This sub-tag operates on a RecArray and returns a new RecArray with the records removed that meet the condition. An exclude condition must contain a column name, operator, and value, and takes the form: "<fieldname> <operator> <value>". Spaces are required between the fieldname, operator, and value.

For example, a RecArray containing a USERID column could be filtered to exclude the current user with:

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE EXCLUDE:'"USERID" == "[LL_REPTAG_USERID /]"' /]
This sub-tag is similar to the FILTER sub-tag, except that it excludes records meeting the condition instead of including them.

See the section on Advanced Notes on Logical Expressions for a list of Operators.

See also: FILTER   

		
EXTSYSACTION:<operation>
The EXTSYSACTION sub-tag creates, updates or deletes external system configurations.

The argument coming from the main tag is the ID of the external system. For the CREATE and UPDATE action the values for the external system configuration is passed as ASSOC that is created by using the ASSOCIATION subtag.

An external system configuration comprises the following fields:

Key	Description	Required	Default
CONN_TYPE	Connection Type	true	
ASURL	Application server endpoint	true	
SCHEMA_VERSION	Schema Version	false	1
ENABLED	Is this configuration enabled?	false	true
BASEURL	Base application server host URL	false	Undefined
USERNAME	Name to use for login	true	
PWD	User password or client secret for OAuth	true	
AUTH_METHOD	Authentication method	false	"BASIC"
CLIENT_ID	Client ID for OAuth	true if AUTH_METHOD is "OAUTH"	Undefined
COMMENT	Comment on this configuration	false	Undefined

To configure OAuth authentication set parameter AUTH_METHOD to OAUTH and assign parameter CLIENT_ID the OAuth client ID and parameter PWD the client secret. Authentication type OAuth is currently only supported by connection type SFInstance.

Example:
[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "CONN_TYPE"      , "ot.sap.c4c.SpiAdapterV2" },
    { "ASURL"          , "https://myhost.acme.com/sap/c4c/odata/v1/c4codataapi" },
    { "SCHEMA_VERSION" , 1 },
    { "ENABLED"        , true },
    { "BASEURL"        , "https://myhost.acme.com" },
    { "USERNAME"       , "hamlet" },
    { "PWD"            , "toBeOrNotToBe" },
    { "COMMENT"        , "External system for EXTSYSACTION tag docu." }
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ExtSysCfg /]
If multilingual display names are to be assigned they can likewise be assembled in an ASSOC and then assigned to configuration key MULTILINGUALS.

Example with multilingual display names:
[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "en" , "Business Application 1" },
    { "de" , "Geschäftsanwendung 1"   },
    { "es" , "Aplicación comercial 1" }
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:MultilingualNames /]
[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "CONN_TYPE"      , "ot.sap.c4c.SpiAdapterV2" },
    { "ASURL"          , "https://myhost.acme.com/sap/c4c/odata/v1/c4codataapi" },
    { "SCHEMA_VERSION" , 1 },
    { "ENABLED"        , true },
    { "BASEURL"        , "https://myhost.acme.com" },
    { "USERNAME"       , "hamlet" },
    { "PWD"            , "toBeOrNotToBe" },
    { "COMMENT"        , "External system for EXTSYSACTION tag docu." },
    { "MULTILINGUALS"  , [LL_REPTAG_!MultilingualNames /] }
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ExtSysCfg /]
Format	Description
EXTSYSACTION:CREATE:	Create an external system configuration. The external system ID is taken from the main tag. All other configuration parameters are passed as ASSOC (see examples above).

Example:
[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "CONN_TYPE" , "ot.sap.c4c.SpiAdapterV2" },
    { "ASURL"     , "https://myhost.acme.com/sap/c4c/odata/v1/c4codataapi" },
    { "USERNAME"  , "hamlet" },
    { "PWD"       , "toBeOrNotToBe" },
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ExtSysCfg /]
 
[LL_REPTAG_"D7K" EXTSYSACTION:CREATE:[LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfg /] /]
The ASSOC in variable ExtSysCfg must contain the following required parameters as described in the table above: CONN_TYPE, ASURL, USERNAME and PWD.
EXTSYSACTION:GET	Get an external system configuration. The external system ID is taken from the main tag.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_"D7K" EXTSYSACTION:GET /]
EXTSYSACTION:UPDATE	Update an external system configuration. The ID of the external system to be updated is taken from the main tag. The parameters to be updated are passed as ASSOC (see examples above).

Example: [LL_REPTAG_"D7K" EXTSYSACTION:UPDATE:[LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfg /] /]
EXTSYSACTION:DELETE	Deletes an external system. The ID of the external system to be deleted is taken from the main tag.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_"D7K" EXTSYSACTION:DELETE /]
EXTSYSACTION:GETALL	Gets all external system configurations. The returned external system configurations contain the additional member REFCOUNT which is the number of business object types that are configured for this external system.

Example:
[LL_REPTAG_"" EXTSYSACTION:GETALL SETVAR:ExtSysCfgList /]
 
[LL_WEBREPORT_FOR DATA:[LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfgList /] VAR:"ExtSysCfg" /]
    <table>
        <tr>
            <td>External System ID</td>
            <td>: [LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfg ASSOC:ID_EXTSYSTEM /]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Connection Type</td>
            <td>: [LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfg ASSOC:CONN_TYPE /]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Reference Count</td>
            <td>: [LL_REPTAG_!ExtSysCfg ASSOC:REFCOUNT /]</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
[LL_WEBREPORT_ENDFOR /]
		
