GETSHAREEXPIRY
This subtag returns the share expiry date or a list of share expiry dates of the items for a valid Content Server node ID or node IDs that are shared.

The list has one entry per node. Each entry is an Assoc of the node ID and the date of the share expiry:

node ID
share expiry date
If a specified node ID of a shared item is queried, the shared expiry for that item is returned. If share expiry date is not set, the value returned will be undefined.

If a specified node ID is not shared, an error is returned.

If a specified node ID does not exist, an error is returned.

The share expiry can only be retrieved if the Content Server user who runs the WebReport has access control rights to view the permissions of the nodes.

Permissions are controlled by the settings in the Permission Page Access section on the Content Server Configure Access Control Admin page (func=admin.AccessControl).
If the setting is set to See Permissions, then the user only requires see permissions to get the list of share expire dates.
If the setting is set to Edit Permissions, then the user will require edit permissions in order to get the list of share expire dates.
		
GETSHAREPARTICIPANTS
This subtag returns a list of the share participants for Content Server node IDs that are shared with Core Share.

The list has one entry per node. Each entry is an Assoc with participant information:

idType ("User", "Pending User", "Group")
id
email
name
role ("Limited", "Viewer", "Collaborator", "Manager", "Owner")
photoUrl
The idType will determine which fields are returned:

User will have an ID, email, name, role, and photoUrl
Pending User will have an email and a name
Group will have an ID, name, role, and photoUrl
If a root share folder is queried, the participants for that folder are returned.

If a root share document is queried, the participants for that document are returned.

If a subnode of a shared folder is queried, the full participant list is returned including participants inherited from the parent folder.

If a node ID of an item that is not shared is specified, an error is returned.

If a node ID that does not exist is specified, an error is returned.

The participants can only be retrieved if the Content Server user who ran the WebReport has access control rights to view the permissions.

Permissions are controlled by the settings in the Permission Page Access section on the Content Server Configure Access Control Admin page (func=admin.AccessControl).
If the setting is set to See Contents, then the user only requires see permissions to get the list of participants.
If the settings are set to Edit Permissions, then the user will require edit permissions in order to get the list of participants.
		
