GROUPACTION:<operation>
Provides the ability to perform actions against groups.
Expects a group ID or name in the main tag, unless otherwise stated.

Action	Description
GROUPACTION:ADD:<group or user ID or name>	Adds a user or group to the group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_"1001" GROUPACTION:ADD:38832 /] adds the user with ID=38832 to the group with ID=1001.
GROUPACTION:CREATE	Expects a group name in the main tag.
Creates a new group, and returns the ID of the new group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_"New group" GROUPACTION:CREATE /] will create a group called "New group".
GROUPACTION:DELETE	Deletes the group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_"1234" GROUPACTION:DELETE /] will delete the group with ID=1234.
GROUPACTION:LEADER:SET:<group or user ID or name>	Sets a user or group as Group Leader of the group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_'1234' GROUPACTION:LEADER:SET:9876 /] sets the user or group with ID=9876 to be the group leader of the group with ID=1234.
GROUPACTION:LEADER:UNSET	Unsets the Group Leader of the group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_'1234' GROUPACTION:GROUPLEADER:UNSET /] unsets the Group Leader of the group with ID=1234.
GROUPACTION:REMOVE:<group or user ID or name>	Removes a user or group from the group.
Note that you can't remove a user from a group whose Department is the same group. In Content Server, a user must be part of a Department.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_'1234' GROUPACTION:REMOVE:9876 /] will remove the user or group with ID=9876 from the group with ID=1234.
GROUPACTION:RENAME:<new group name>	Renames the group.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_'1234' GROUPACTION:RENAME:"New group name" /] will rename the group with ID=1234 to "New group name".
See also: USERACTION   

		
GROUPBY:<column to group by>
Groups a RecArray data structure by the column provided and returns counts of all grouped row values in that column.

Example syntax - simple grouping:

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE GROUPBY:"Type" /]

This will take the data source and group the filtered data by the "Type" column.

Ungrouped input returned by [LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE /]:

V{
<'DataID','ParentID','SubType','Name','Status','Reviewer','Type'>
<239582,239579,144,'Sample Document 1.docx','Placeholder','Bob Smith','Contract'>
<239583,239582,144,'Sample Document 2.docx','Placeholder','Bob Smith','Program'>
<239586,239582,144,'Sample Document 3.docx','Final','Ted Jones','Contract'>
<239589,239582,144,'Sample Document 4.docx','Placeholder','Sarah McGuire','SOP'>
<239592,239582,144,'Sample Document 5.docx','Draft','Jill Hackett','User guide'>
<239595,239582,144,'Sample Document 6.docx','Draft','Jill Hackett','Contract'>
<239598,239582,144,'Sample Document 7.docx','Final','Jill Hackett','User guide'>
<239601,239582,144,'Sample Document 8.docx','Final','Ted Jones','Plan'>
<239604,239582,144,'Sample Document 9.docx','Placeholder','Jill Hackett','Contract'>
}

Grouped ouput:

V{
<'Type','Count'>
<'Contract',4>
<'Program',1>
<'SOP',1>
<'User guide',2>
<'Plan',1>
}

Example syntax - filtering, grouping and converting to JSON:

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE FILTER:'"Reviewer" == "Jill Hackett"' GROUPBY:"Type" TOJSON /]

This will take the data source, filter the data for all rows where the Reviewer is Jill Hackett, group the filtered data by the "Type" column and then convert the output to JSON.

Filtered, grouped output converted to JSON:

[
{ "Type":"User guide", "Count":2},
{ "Type":"Contract", "Count":2}
]

Note:The Group By action is case insensitive. This means if one row has the value 'Contract' and another has the value 'contract', both will be grouped together under the same count.

See also: FILTER   TOJSON   RECARRAY   

		
