LOGFAULT:<fault type>:<severity level>
This sub-tag can be used to log faults to the System Fault Log. Expects an error message in the main tag. If the main tag is blank, then the sub-tag will do nothing.

The sub-tag takes two arguments.

The first argument is the fault type.

Valid values are:

SYSTEM for a system fault (visible to System Administrators).
BUSINESS for a business fault (visible to Business Administrators).

The second argument is the severity level.

Valid values are:

INFO
WARNING
ERROR
SEVERE
CRITICAL

Examples:

[LL_REPTAG_"A system fault has occurred." LOGFAULT:SYSTEM:INFO /] will log a system fault in the System Fault Log with Severity = "Info", Event Type = "WebReport System Fault" and Details = "Raised from WebReport ID: <WebReport ID>. A system fault has occurred.".

[LL_REPTAG_"A business fault has occurred." LOGFAULT:BUSINESS:CRITICAL /] will log a business fault in the System Fault Log with Severity = "Critical", Event Type = "WebReport Business Fault" and Details = "Raised from WebReport ID: <WebReport ID>. A business fault has occurred.".

See also: ONERROR   

		
