MIGRATIONACTION:<operation>
The MIGRATIONACTION sub-tag offers operations for migration administration. The sub-tag itself behaves like other WebReport sub-tags. This implies that users, who are not allowed to perform an operation using the regular user interface, also cannot run the MIGRATIONACTION operation.

Before you can start a migration process, you must define, which items you want to be migrated to which type of workspace. You can define such a mapping now and run it at a later time. With the status of a mapping, you can control whether it can be processed or not.

The following key-value pairs are supported as parameters for adding and updating migration mappings:

AREA=<(only for cases, contracts, and binders): Workspace area for which this binder, contract, and case is valid> // Valid values can be found at MIGRATIONINFO:AREAS. Only Area ids are allowed.

OBJECTTYPE=<A Content Server Object Type> // List of allowed object types can be found at MIGRATIONINFO:OBJECTTYPES. Only Ids are allowed.

PATH=<Path to the location that contains items that you want to migrate> // Only IDs are allowed.

RECURSIVE=<Converts all nested sub-elements as well> // Optional argument. Default is TRUE.

BWSTEMPLATE=<Workspace template that will be applied to the migrated workspaces> // Only IDs are allowed.

CATEGORY=<Category for the converted business workspaces> // Optional argument. Only IDs are allowed.

DURATIONCATEGORY=<Duration category for the contract file duration tab> // Optional argument. Only IDs are allowed.

FILTERCRITERIA=<Search for items that start with, end with, contains, or exactly match to a string> // Optional argument. Valid values: [1=startswith, 2=endswith, 3=contains, 4=exact]. Also, can be found at MIGRATIONINFO:FILTERTYPES.

FILTERTEXT=<Apply a filter to the name field>// Optional argument.

STATUS=<Status of the migration mapping> // Optional argument. Default is Open. Valid values: [ 1=Open, 2=Active ].

Operation	Description
MIGRATIONACTION:ADD:<key>=<value>...	Creates a new mapping to convert items to business workspaces. The parameters with the keys OBJECTTYPE, PATH, and BWSTEMPLATE are mandatory. AREA is mandatory for binders, contracts, and cases.
MIGRATIONACTION:CONVERTTOBWS:<Template Id>:<Workspace Type node Id>:<New node name>:<Area Id>	Converts a container template to a workspace template. Template Id and Workspace Type node Id are mandatory arguments. New node name and Area Id are optional arguments.
MIGRATIONACTION:DELETE:<{Mapping Id(s)}>	Deletes the mappings with single or list of Mapping Ids.
Examples: MIGRATIONACTION:DELETE:1 / MIGRATIONACTION:DELETE:{1,2,3}.
MIGRATIONACTION:UPDATE:<Mapping Id>:<key>=<value>...	Updates the mapping with id <Mapping Id>. The parameters that can be used for ADD will also work here.
MIGRATIONACTION:RUN:<{Mapping Id(s)}>	Executes the active mappings with <Mapping Id(s)> as an optional parameter. Mapping Id(s) can be a single mapping id or a list of mapping ids.
Examples: MIGRATIONACTION:RUN / MIGRATIONACTION:RUN:1 / MIGRATIONACTION:RUN:{1,2,3}.
See also: MIGRATIONINFO   

		
