NODEACTION:<operation>
This sub-tag offers powerful capabilities to perform various actions against nodes within Content Server and, as such, its effects should be carefully understood before usage. The sub-tag itself behaves like other WebReports sub-tags in that NODEACTION will not allow the user running the report to perform an action (e.g. a move) that they would not be able to perform via the regular interface.

Action	Operation	Description
ADDVER	NODEACTION:ADDVER:TEXT:<text string>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Adds a version to it containing the value specified in text string.
NODEACTION:ADDVER:<document>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Adds a version to it containing the contents of the latest version of the document specified in the document parameter.

Optionally append :INHERITATTRS:SOURCE to inherit the category and attribute data from the source document.
NODEACTION:ADDVER:<document>:<version number>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Adds a version to it containing the contents of the version of the document specified in the document and version number parameters.

Optionally append :INHERITATTRS:SOURCE to inherit the category and attribute data from the source document.
By default NODEACTION:ADDVER will add a Minor version to the target document.
To add the new version as a Major version to a document that uses Advanced versioning, append the :MAJOR option.

For example:
NODEACTION:ADDVER:<document>:MAJOR

If :MAJOR is used on a document that uses Standard versioning, the :MAJOR option will be ignored and a version will still be added to the document.
CLASSIFICATION	NODEACTION:CLASSIFICATION:ADD:<classification ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Adds the classification specified in the classification ID argument to it.
NODEACTION:CLASSIFICATION:REMOVE:<classification ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Removes the classification specified in the classification ID argument from it.
Use RMACTION:RMCLASSIFICATION to work with Records Management classifications.
COLLECTION	NODEACTION:COLLECTION:ADDITEM:<collection ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Adds the node to the collection specified in the collection ID argument.
NODEACTION:COLLECTION:ADDITEM:<collection ID>:CURRENT	Same as previous except that only the current version of the node will be added to the collection.
NODEACTION:COLLECTION:COPYITEM:<source collection ID>:<target collection ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Copies the node from the collection specified in the source collection ID argument to the collection specified in the target collection ID argument.
NODEACTION:COLLECTION:MOVEITEM:<source collection ID>:<target collection ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Moves the node from the collection specified in the source collection ID argument to the collection specified in the target collection ID argument.
NODEACTION:COLLECTION:REMOVEITEM:<collection ID>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Removes the node from the collection specified in the collection ID argument.
NODEACTION:COLLECTION:REMOVEITEM:<collection ID>:<version number>	Same as previous except that only the specified version of the node is removed from the collection (Content Server 10 or above only).
COPY	NODEACTION:COPY:<container>	Expects a dataid from the main tag. Copies this node to the location specified in container. Takes all versions and uses the same name.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:CURRENT	Same as previous but only takes the latest (current) version of the source document. If the source object is a container only the latest version of items within the container will be copied.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITATTRS:DESTINATION	Inherits the category and attribute data from the destination location.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITATTRS:MERGED	Merges the category and attribute data from the source node and the destination location.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITATTRS:SOURCE	Retains the source category and attribute data when copied to the destination location.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITPERMS	Inherits the permissions from the destination container.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITRMOFF	Default behavior for NODEACTION is as if the action occurred through the Content Server interface; that is a copied node will inherit RM Classifications from the new parent container. This option can be used to stop the inheritance of the RM Classification. If an existing RM Classification is already applied to the node that is about to be copied then that RM Classification will be retained after the copy event has occurred. This option can be used to override the "Records Management Administration", "Managed Objects", "Inherit from" options but cannot be used to force the inheritance of an RM Classification if the appropriate RM settings are not present.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITSUPPLEMENTALMARKINGS:<option>	Sets the inheritance for Supplemental Markings.

Valid options are:
IGNORE, which does not change the Supplemental Markings on the item being copied.
MERGE, which merges the Supplemental Markings on the item being copied with the Supplemental Markings of the new container.
REPLACE, which replaces the Supplemental Markings on the item being copied with the Supplemental Markings of the new container.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:INHERITSECURITYCLEARANCE:<option>	Sets the inheritance for Security Clearance Level.

Valid options are:
IGNORE, which does not change the Security Clearance Level on the item being copied.
UPGRADE, which upgrades the Security Clearance Level of the item being copied to the Security Clearance Level of the new container. If the new container has a lower Security Clearance Level, the item retains its Security Clearance setting.
NODEACTION:COPY:<container>:NEWNAME:<name>	Uses the optional NEWNAME parameter to specify a new name for the destination node.
