PREV
Return the same column from the previous row of data. If this sub-tag is used on the first row of data, a blank string is returned.

		
QUOTE
or
QUOTE:<format>
The QUOTE sub-tag adds either single or double quotation marks to the string in the main tag, with any matching embedded quotation marks escaped.

The default is a single quote. Use QUOTE:'"' to use a double quote instead.

For example:

[LL_REPTAG_"It's Tuesday" /] returns It's Tuesday
[LL_REPTAG_"It's Tuesday" QUOTE /] returns 'It\'s Tuesday'
[LL_REPTAG_"It's Tuesday" QUOTE:'"' /] returns "It's Tuesday"

		
RANGE:<start index>
or
RANGE:<start index>:<end index>
For any list, formatted as: {'item1','item2'}, returns a range from the original list based on a specified start index and an optional end index. This sub-tag is identical to the SLICE sub-tag but only works with LISTs. All indices count starting at 1 (one) so the slice will include all characters starting from and including the <start index> and concluding with and including the <end index> (if one is specified). If end index is omitted or exceeds the total length of the string then the remainder of the string is used. A LIST follows the Content Server LIST convention where the first character is a {, the last character is a } and each element is separated by a comma. This output of this sub-tag is a list in the same format. A LIST can be de-referenced using the LIST sub-tag.

RANGE Examples:

These different examples of the RANGE sub-tag show the different results which would be produced, assuming the associated tag contained the list:

{'Apple','Pear','Orange','Mango'}
RANGE:3 would return: {'Orange','Mango'}
RANGE:2:3 would return: {'Pear','Orange'}
RANGE:3:100 would return: {'Orange','Mango'}
RANGE:2:3 LIST:1 would return: 'Pear'
		
REAL
Explicitly casts data as type Real.

		
REC
The REC sub-tag operates on a DataID, and returns the related row from the WebNodes view. For example:

[LL_REPTAG_'2000' REC /],
returns the WebNodes record for the Enterprise:

R<'OWNERID'=-2000,'PARENTID'=-1,'DATAID'=2000,'NAME'='Enterprise', ... >.
The sub-tag also accepts a "DTREE" parameter, which returns the DTree record for the provided DataID.

		
RECARRAY:<format>
Allows sorting and indexing of the Content Server RECARRAY data type.
If the column extracted from the data source is a RECARRAY (a Content Server data structure consisting of a LIST of RECORDs), the value of the field specified by <rowIndex> and <colIndex> or <fieldName> is returned (and only that value).

Sort the RECARRAY by appending up to 10 parameters to determine on which columns to sort.
The parameters can be a column index or a field name, and can be prefixed with a minus sign to sort that column in descending order.

Note, this sub-tag can be used repetitively and/or in combination with other sub-tags such as ASSOC and LIST to access information in complex data structures.

Examples:

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE RECARRAY:SORT:"PARENTID":-2 /] will sort the data by PARENTID ascending, then by column 2 descending.

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE RECARRAY:SORT:"PARENTID":"-NAME" /] will sort the data by PARENTID ascending, then by NAME descending.

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE RECARRAY:1:2 /] will return the value of the second column of the first row of the RECARRAY.

[LL_REPTAG_DATASOURCE RECARRAY:1:NAME /] will return the value of the NAME column of the first row of the RECARRAY.

See also: ASSOC   LIST   RECORD   

		
RECORD:<index>
or
RECORD:<fieldName>
Allows indexing of the Content Server RECORD data type. If the column extracted from a data source is a RECORD (a Content Server data structure) the value of the field specified by <index> or <fieldName> is returned (and only that value). The <index> argument will only work if the data does not contain commas or equals signs. It is recommended that <fieldName> is used instead.

Note, this sub-tag can be used repetitively and/or in combination with other sub-tags such as ASSOC and LIST to access information in complex data structures.

See also: ASSOC   LIST   RECARRAY   

		
REDIRECT
Redirects the browser to the URL specified in the main tag.

		
REMINDERACTION:<parms>
Provides the ability to add, update and delete reminders against the node returned from the main tag.

Action	Description
REMINDERACTION:ADD:<arguments>	Adds a reminder to the node returned from the main tag.

Use the ASSOCATION sub-tag to pass in the following arguments:
Argument	Description
TYPE	Reminder type.
PRIORITY	Valid values are HIGH, MEDIUM or LOW.
DUEDATE	Use the ASSOCACTION sub-tag to optionally pass in Due Date data containing one of the following arguments:

Argument	Description
ON:<start date>	The date that the reminder will start on, for example, ON:"2022-12-31".
IN:<In assoc>	Use the ASSOCATION sub-tag to pass in an In assoc containing the following arguments:

Argument	Description
VALUE	Integer between 1 and 99.
UNIT	Valid values are DAYS, WEEKS, MONTHS or YEARS.
PERIODIC:<Periodic assoc>	Use the ASSOCACTION sub-tag to pass in Periodic data containing the following arguments:

Argument	Description
TYPE	Valid values are DAILY, WEEKLY, MONTHLY or YEARLY.
VALUE	Required for WEEKLY and MONTHLY reminders.
Integer between 1 and 9.
DAY	Required for MONTHLY and YEARLY reminders.
Sets whether the reminder will occur on a fixed date (for example, the 1st of the month), or a specific day (for example, the last Wednesday of the month).
Valid values are FIXED or WEEKDAY.
DAYS	Required for WEEKLY, and MONTHLY and YEARLY WEEKDAY reminders.
List containing the days of the week that the reminder will occur.
Valid values are MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY and SUNDAY.
For example, DAYS:{"MONDAY","WEDNESDAY","FRIDAY"}.
DUEON	Required for MONTHLY and YEARLY reminders.
The date that the reminder will occur.
For MONTHLY FIXED reminders, this must be an integer between 1 and 31, for example, DUEON:15 if the reminder is due on the 15th of the month.
For WEEKDAY reminders, this must be a list containing any of the following values: 1, 2, 3, 4 or LAST, for example, DUEON:{1,3,"LAST"}.
The numbers denote the first, second, third and fourth weeks of the month, and "LAST" denotes the last week of the month.
For YEARLY FIXED reminders, this must be a Due On assoc containing the following arguments:

Argument	Description
DAY	The day that the reminder should occur on.
Integer between 1 and 31.
MONTH	The month that the reminder should occur on.
Integer between 1 and 12.
BUSINESSDAY	Required for MONTHLY FIXED reminders.
Sets whether the reminder must be on a business day.
Valid values are TRUE or FALSE.
MONTHS	Required for YEARLY WEEKDAY reminders.
List containing the months of the year that the reminder will occur. Valid values are integers between 1 and 12, for example, MONTHS:{2,8,12} for a reminder to occur in February, August and December.
STARTDATE	The date that the reminder will start on, for example, STARTDATE:"2022-12-31".
ENDDATE	The date that the reminder will end on, for example, STARTDATE:"2023-12-31".
Omit this argument if the reminder is open-ended.

If the reminder type is set to activate immediately, the DUEDATE argument does not need to be supplied.
ACTIVATION	Use the ASSOCACTION sub-tag to optionally pass in Activation data containing the following arguments:

Argument	Description
VALUE	Number of days/weeks/months/years prior to the due date that the reminder will be activated.
Integer between 0 and 99.
UNIT	Valid values are DAYS, WEEKS, MONTHS or YEARS.
BUSINESSDAY	Sets whether the activation date must be a business day.
Valid values are TRUE or FALSE.

If the reminder type is configured to activate immediately, the ACTIVATION argument does not need to be supplied.
ESCALATION	Use the ASSOCACTION sub-tag to optionally pass in Escalation data containing the following arguments:

Argument	Description
ENABLED	Sets whether the Escalation settings of the reminder type are enabled, if they are defined as changeable.
Valid values are TRUE or FALSE.
VALUE	Integer between 1 and 99.
UNIT	Valid values are DAYS, WEEKS, MONTHS or YEARS.
WHEN	Sets whether the escalation is triggered after or prior to the reminder's due date. Valid values are AFTER or PRIORTO.
BUSINESSDAY	Sets whether the escalation date must be a business day.
Valid values are TRUE or FALSE.
ASSIGNTO	List containing user/group IDs that the escalation is assigned to, for example, ASSIGNTO:{1000,1001}.
DESCRIPTION	Optional description of the reminder.
ASSIGNTO	List containing user/group IDs that the reminder is assigned to, for example, ASSIGNTO:{1000,1001}.

If the reminder type is configured to activate immediately, the ASSIGNTO argument can only contain one user ID.
Examples:

1. Create a reminder to occur on a specific date.

[// Create ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE and PRIORITY arguments in ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"TimesheetReminder" SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PRIORITY":"HIGH" SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Create DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]

[// Populate ON argument in DueDateAssoc.

[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ON":"2022-12-31" SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]

[// Populate DUEDATE argument in ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DUEDATE":[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc /] SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Create ActivationAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ActivationAssoc /]

[// Populate VALUE, UNIT and BUSINESSDAY values in ActivationAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ActivationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":2 SETVAR:ActivationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ActivationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"UNIT":"WEEKS" SETVAR:ActivationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ActivationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"BUSINESSDAY":"TRUE" SETVAR:ActivationAssoc /]

[// Populate ACTIVATION, DESCRIPTION and ASSIGNTO values in ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ACTIVATION":[LL_REPTAG_!ActivationAssoc /] SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DESCRIPTION":"Description" SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ASSIGNTO":{1000} SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Add the reminder.
[LL_REPTAG_'<node ID>' REMINDERACTION:ADD:[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc /] /]
2. Create a reminder to occur in a set amount of time in the future.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create InAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:InAssoc /]

[// Populate VALUE and UNIT arguments in InAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!InAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":"10" SETVAR:InAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!InAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"UNIT":"MONTHS" SETVAR:InAssoc /]

[// Populate IN argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"IN":[LL_REPTAG_!InAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
3. Create a daily reminder.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, STARTDATE and ENDDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"DAILY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ENDDATE":"2022-12-31" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
4. Create an open-ended weekly reminder.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, VALUE, DAYS and STARTDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"WEEKLY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":5 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAYS":{ "MONDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "FRIDAY" } SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
5. Create an open-ended reminder, every five months, on the 10th of the month (or nearest business day).

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, VALUE, DAY, DUEON, BUSINESSDAY and STARTDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"MONTHLY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":5 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAY":"FIXED" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DUEON":10 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"BUSINESSDAY":"TRUE" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
6. Create an open-ended reminder, every five months, on the first, third and last Monday, Wedneday and Fridays of the month.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, VALUE, DAY, DUEON, DAYS and STARTDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"MONTHLY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":5 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAY":"WEEKDAY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DUEON":{1,3,"LAST"} SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAYS":{"MONDAY","WEDNESDAY","FRIDAY"} SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
7. Create an open-ended reminder, every five years, on the 10th of February of the month.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, VALUE and DAY arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"YEARLY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":5 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAY":"FIXED" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Create DueOnAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:DueOnAssoc /]

[// Populate DAY and MONTH arguments in DueOnAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueOnAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAY":10 SETVAR:DueOnAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!DueOnAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"MONTH":2 SETVAR:DueOnAssoc /]

[// Populate DUEON, BUSINESSDAY and STARTDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DUEON":[LL_REPTAG_!DueOnAssoc /] SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"BUSINESSDAY":"FALSE" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
8. Create an open-ended reminder, every five years, on the first, third and last Monday, Wedneday and Fridays of the second, eighth and twelfth months.

Use the same syntax as example 1, except change the DueDateAssoc as follows:

[// Create PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, VALUE, DAY, DUEON, DAYS, MONTHS and STARTDATE arguments in PeriodicAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"YEARLY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":5 SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAY":"WEEKDAY" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DUEON":{1,3,"LAST"} SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"DAYS":{"MONDAY","WEDNESDAY","FRIDAY"} SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"MONTHS":{2,8,12} SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"STARTDATE":"2022-12-01" SETVAR:PeriodicAssoc /]

[// Populate PERIODIC argument in DueDateAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!DueDateAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PERIODIC":[LL_REPTAG_!PeriodicAssoc /] SETVAR:DueDateAssoc /]
9. Create a reminder of a type which is configured to activate immediately.

[// Create ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Populate TYPE, PRIORITY and ASSIGNTO arguments in ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"TYPE":"Timesheet Late Reminder" SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"PRIORITY":"HIGH" SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ASSIGNTO":{1000} SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]

[// Add the reminder.
[LL_REPTAG_'<node ID>' REMINDERACTION:ADD:[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc /] /]
10. Include escalation details, if the reminder type has changeable escalation defined.

Use the same syntax as example 1, and add escalation details as follows:

[// Create EscalationAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]

[// Populate ENABLED, VALUE, UNIT, WHEN, BUSINESSDAY and ASSIGNTO arguments in EscalationAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ENABLED":"TRUE" SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"VALUE":7 SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"UNIT":"YEARS" SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"WHEN":"AFTER" SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"BUSINESSDAY":"FALSE" SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]
[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ASSIGNTO":"{1000}" SETVAR:EscalationAssoc /]

[// Populate ESCALATION argument in ReminderAssoc.
[LL_REPTAG_!ReminderAssoc ASSOCACTION:ADD:"ESCALATION":[LL_REPTAG_!EscalationAssoc /] SETVAR:ReminderAssoc /]
REMINDERACTION:UPDATE:<arguments>	Updates a reminder against the node returned from the main tag.

This argument accepts the same arguments as ADD (above), with the following addition:

Argument	Description
ID	ID of the reminder being updated, for example, ID:58.
REMINDERACTION:DELETE:<reminder ID>	Deletes a reminder from the node returned from the main tag.
See also: ASSOCACTION   

		
RENDITIONACTION:<operation>
This sub-tag offers capabilities to perform various actions against a rendition of a version of a node within Content Server.
It expects a node ID from the main tag.

Operation	Description
DELETE:<version number>:<rendition type>	Deletes the rendition of the specified type from the specified version of the node.
UPDATE:MIMETYPE:<new MIME type>:<version number>:<rendition type>	Updates the MIME type of the specified rendition of the version of the node.
UPDATE:STORAGEPROVIDER:<new Storage Provider type>:<version number>:<rendition type>	Changes the Storage Provider of the specified rendition of the version of the node.
		
REPLACE:<parm1>:<parm2>
Performs a "replace all" action on the items of data pulled from the data source. All occurrences of the <parm1> string are replaced by <parm2>. E.g.:

[LL_REPTAG=PRIORITY REPLACE:"3":"Low" /]
This example would result in all occurrences of the number '3' in the Priority field being replaced with 'Low'. Note there can be no spaces between REPLACE, parm1 and parm2. Use only the colon separator.

		
RMACTION:<operation>
Provides the ability to perform various actions against Records Management data found on the Records Detail tab of Records (Content Server nodes such as documents) that are being managed with the Records Management module.

If Records Management is not enabled then this sub-tag will return nothing for all options.

Action	Operation	Description
ACCESSION	RMACTION:ACCESSION:<new value>	Updates the Accession field.
ADDRESSEE	RMACTION:ADDRESSEE:<new value>	Updates the Addressee(s) field.
AUTHOR	RMACTION:AUTHOR:<new value>	Updates the Author or Originator field.
CYCLEPERIOD	RMACTION:CYCLEPERIOD:<new value>	Updates the Cycle Period field. Valid values are:
0 (None)
1 (Monthly)
2 (Semi-Annual based on calendar year)
3 (Quarterly based on calendar year)
7 (Weekly)
12 (Annual based on calendar year)
365 (Daily)
ESSENTIAL	RMACTION:ESSENTIAL:<new value>	Updates the Essential field. Indicate the 3 letter code.
FINALIZE	RMACTION:FINALIZE	Finalizes the record. Optionally append :APPLYTOSUBITEMS to finalize sub-items as well as the node in the main tag.
LASTREVIEWDATE	RMACTION:LASTREVIEWDATE:<new value>	Updates the Last Review Date field. Passing an empty <new value> will clear the field.
NEXTREVIEWDATE	RMACTION:NEXTREVIEWDATE:<new value>	Updates the Next Review Date field. Passing an empty <new value> will clear the field.
OFFICIAL	RMACTION:OFFICIAL:<new value>	Updates the Official field. Value can be set to TRUE or FALSE.
ORIGINATINGORG	RMACTION:ORIGINATINGORG:<new value>	Updates the Originating Organization field.
OTHERADDRESSEE	RMACTION:OTHERADDRESSEE:<new value>	Updates the Other Addressee(s) field.
RECEIVEDDATE	RMACTION:RECEIVEDDATE:<new value>	Updates the Received Date field. Passing an empty <new value> will clear the field.
RECORDDATE	RMACTION:RECORDDATE:<new value>	Updates the Record Date field.
RMCLASSIFICATION	RMACTION:RMCLASSIFICATION:ADD:<classification ID>	Adds the Records Management classification specified in the classification ID argument to the record.
If the record already has a Records Management classification then the existing classification will be removed and replaced with the new one.
RMACTION:RMCLASSIFICATION:REMOVE:<classification ID>	Removes the Records Management classification specified in the classification ID argument from the record.
SERIALIZE	RMACTION:SERIALIZE:<field name>	Returns a JSON representation of the field definition.
SHOW will need to be appended to return the value to the browser, or to allow it be further modified by other subtags.
STATUS	RMACTION:STATUS:<new value>	Updates the Status field. Indicate the 3 letter code.
STATUSDATE	RMACTION:STATUSDATE:<new value>	Updates the Status Date field.
STORAGEMEDIUM	RMACTION:STORAGEMEDIUM:<new value>	Updates the Storage Medium field. Indicate the 3 letter code.
SUBJECT	RMACTION:SUBJECT:<new value>	Updates the Subject field.
See also: RMCLASS   RMHOLDACTION   RMHOLDINFO   RMINFO   RMPERMCHECK   RMTYPE   RMXREFACTION   RMXREFINFO   RSI   RSISCHEDULE   

		
RMCLASS:<parm>
Provides metadata information unique to RM Classification objects. Requires the dataid of the RM Classification to be returned from the main tag. If needing to access details of an RM Classification from the node to which it is applied the RMINFO sub-tag can be used: [LL_REPTAG=DATAID RMINFO:CLASSID RMCLASS:xxx /]. RSI details can be accessed in a similar fashion with the RSI sub-tag. E.g: [LL_REPTAG=DATAID RMINFO:CLASSID RMCLASS:RSI RSI:URL /] would get the URL to open an RSI based purely on the dataid of the node the RSI/RM Classification is applied to.

