ROLEACTION:<operation>
The ROLEACTION sub-tag offers operations for roles. These operations are very powerful and thus should be used carefully. The sub-tag itself behaves like other WebReport sub-tags. This implies that users, who are not allowed to perform an operation using the regular user interface, also cannot run the ROLEACTION operation.
The sub-tag supports the SPM (Standard Permission Model) and the WPM (Work Items Permission Model). Please see the sub-tag PERMACTION for a detailed description of the supported permission models and its permission constants.

The following key value pairs are supported as parameters for adding and updating roles:
NAME=<the name of the role>
DESCRIPTION=<the description of the role>
SETASLEADER //Sets the role as the leader role
MEMBERS=<single user or group id or list of user or group IDs>
PERMS=<list of permissions> // The permissions can be either an integer value or a list of permission constants like SEE or MODIFY.
APPLYTO=<Integer value> // 0=This item, 1=Sub-items, 2=This item and sub-items, 3=This item and immediate non container sub-items
INCLUDESUBTYPES=<list of sub types> // Roles are usually not added to WPM sub-items like TaskList or Channel, except for those subtypes, which are listed here.

Operation	Description
ROLEACTION:ADD:<key>=<value>...	Creates the role and adds it to the node. The node must be a workspace. The parameter with the key NAME is mandatory. The return value contains the role ID. If the parameter with the key APPLYTO is set, then the result also contains information about the number of processed sub-items (success and failure). The user must have the 'Edit permissions' right on the workspace to use this operation.
ROLEACTION:ADDTONODE:<role ID>:<key>=<value>...	Adds the role with ID <role ID> to the current node. The parameters with the keys PERMS, APPLYTO, INCLUDESUBTYPES are supported. The parent workspace must contain the specified role. If the parameter with the key APPLYTO is set, then the result also contains information about the number of processed sub-items (success and failure). The user must have the 'Edit permissions' right on the node to use this operation.
ROLEACTION:UPDATE:<role ID>:<key>=<value>...	Updates the role with ID <role ID> for the current node. The parameters with the keys NAME, DESCRIPTION, SETASLEADER and MEMBERS are only supported if the node is a workspace. If the parameter with the key APPLYTO is set, then the result also contains information about the number of processed sub-items (success and failure). The user must have 'Edit permissions' on the node to use this operation. However, users who are members of the leader role, can set members without the 'Edit permissions' right.
ROLEACTION:REMOVE:<role ID>	Deletes the role with ID <role ID> for the current node and all sub-items. The user must the have 'Edit permissions' right on the node to use this operation.
See also: ROLEINFO   PERMACTION   

		
ROLEINFO:<operation>
The ROLEINFO sub-tag returns information about the roles for the current node. The role contains information about the id, name, description, permissions, members, whether the role is set as the leader role, and the id of the parent node if the role is inherited from it.

Operation	Description
ROLEINFO	Returns information about the roles for the current node.
ROLEINFO:<role ID>	Returns information about the role with id <role ID> for the current node.
See also: ROLEACTION   

		
ROUND:<round number>
or
ROUND:CEIL
or
ROUND:FLOOR
Rounds a numeric value by the specified ROUND parameter. If no ROUND parameter is specified, it defaults to 2. Accepts CEIL and FLOOR as optional parameters to force rounding upwards or downwards to the closest Integer.

Examples:

25.479 ROUND:2 would return: 25.48
45 ROUND:3 would return: 45.000// Zeroes are padded
50.99 ROUND:0 would return: 51
-4.545 ROUND:1 would return: -4.5
25.479 ROUND:CEIL would return: 26
50.99 ROUND:FLOOR would return: 50
The ROUND parameter must be greater than or equal to 0 and an integer. An error occurs if the tag does not contain a valid integer or real number. Zeroes are padded to the specified ROUND parameter if no decimal portion is present (See second example).

		
RPAD:<pad char>:<width>
Add padding characters to the right of existing data. Add enough characters to fill the field up to the specified width . If there is a mantissa, then only the width of the number following the decimal points is used.

For example, given a data tag returning the number 123.456

[LL_REPTAG_1 RPAD:9:5 /]
would return: 123.45699.

Given a data tag returning the number 123

[LL_REPTAG_1 RPAD:9:5 /]
would return: 12399.

		
