RUNSQL
This sub-tag is used to run a LiveReport, and returns the results as a RecArray.
The main tag must contain the DataID of a LiveReport.
Parameters passed to RUNSQL are interpreted as &inputLabel1, &inputLabel2, etc.

For example,

[LL_REPTAG_'9999' RUNSQL:"JohnDoe" /],
This executes the LiveReport with DataID 9999 and passes in the parameter &inputLabel1=JohnDoe.

If the LiveReport runs an UPDATE or DELETE statement then the RecArray will contain a single record containing "rowCount", which will be populated by the number of rows updated or deleted.

		
RUNSWR
This sub-tag provides a sub-tag syntax for calling a sub-WebReport. The following examples demonstrate how a sub-WebReport is normally called with the [LL_WEBREPORT_SUBWEBREPORT /] tag:

[LL_WEBREPORT_SUBWEBREPORT NODEID:68873 PARM:inputLabel1:299 PARM:myStatus:"awaiting review" /].
This can be rewritten with the RUNSWR sub-tag as follows:

[LL_REPTAG_'68873' RUNSWR:inputLabel1:299:myStatus:"awaiting review" /].
Both approaches produce the same result, except the second approach allows further sub-tags to be added to the tag. For example:

[LL_REPTAG_'68873' RUNSWR:inputLabel1:299:myStatus:"awaiting review" DECODE:0:"false":1:"true" /].
If the destination of the sub-WebReport is a Content Server Node, then the nodeID can be returned to the calling WebReport by adding the SHOWNODEID argument to end of the RUNSWR call. For example:

[LL_REPTAG_$mySubReport RUNSWR:SHOWNODEID /]
[LL_REPTAG_$mySubReport RUNSWR:inputLabel1:299:myStatus:"awaiting review":SHOWNODEID /]
See Sub-WebReports for more information.

See also: LL_WEBREPORT_SUBWEBREPORT   

		
RUNTEMPLATE
Calling RUNTEMPLATE is similar to calling a sub-WebReport and has the same syntax as RUNSWR. However, there are some key differences:

The template ignores its own parameters, constants, and data source.
The context from the calling report is shared with the template. That means constants, variables, parameters, and the data source from the calling report are visible in the template.
The template can change variables, but these changes are not reflected in the calling report.
The RUNTEMPLATE sub-tag can also be used to run templates located on the filesystem.

See also: RUNSWR   

		
