SECURETOKEN
or
SECURETOKEN:FULLPARM
This sub-tag will generate a secure request token for a specific action or WebReport.

The data specified by the data tag is used as part of the key, and can be any string or number, but should match whatever action is expected in Content Server.

WebReports expects the dataID of the WebReport being run, but most Content Server actions expect a string such as "Action-Copy".

Adding the FULLPARM option will return the name of the Content Server token parameter as it will appear in a URL.

By default, the returned token is escaped so that any plus signs (+) do not get stripped during request submission.

[LL_REPTAG_"Action-Move" SECURETOKEN /] will return a secure request token for moving a node in Content Server.
[LL_REPTAG_"Action-Move" SECURETOKEN:FULLPARM /] will return the token including the URL parameter name, eg: "&secureRequestToken=".
[LL_REPTAG_$WR1 SECURETOKEN /] returns a unique token required to execute a WebReport that is set as the "WR1" constant.
When using the optional :FULLPARM parameter, the return value can be converted to a hidden HTML input field using the URLTOPOST sub-tag:

[LL_REPTAG_"Action-Move" SECURETOKEN:FULLPARM URLTOPOST /]
returns
<INPUT TYPE="HIDDEN" NAME="securerequesttoken" VALUE="<token>">.
<INPUT TYPE="HIDDEN" NAME="securerequesttoken" VALUE="[LL_REPTAG_'Action-Move' SECURETOKEN /]">
returns
<INPUT TYPE="HIDDEN" NAME="securerequesttoken" VALUE="<token>">.
A logout token can be retrieved from the session cache (if it exists) using the following syntax:

[LL_REPTAG_"logout" SECURETOKEN /]
		
