VERSIONCAT:<parm>
Returns information about the Categories and Attributes associated with a specific version of the current object ID. This sub-tag supports both attribute sets and multi-value attributes through use of the MV and SET operators.

For example: [LL_REPTAG=DATAID VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:<attribute>:DISPLAY /] will return the attribute value stored in the category whose display name or ID matches the <category> value and the attribute whose display name or ID matches the <attribute> value for any attribute type for version <vernum> of the node. If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute or an attribute set a comma-separated list of values will be returned.

To return Category data for the latest version of a node see the CAT sub-tag.

Syntax	Description
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on the presence of one or more categories assigned to the version of the node.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:JSARRAY	This is a unique option for the VERSIONCAT sub-tag which results in a JavaScript object representation of all the category and attribute data (including full support for sets and multi-values) for the version of the node. For detailed information on this feature see the Category JSARRAY advanced help.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:RAW	This option results in a flat oscript representation of all the category and attribute data associated with the version of the node.

See the Request as Data Source advanced help for how to use the output of this, and related tags, as the data source to another WebReport.

See the TOJSON sub-tag for how to convert this into a data structure that can be interpreted by JavaScript in the client.

See related tags LLURL:FUNCTIONMENU:RAW and LLURL:ADDITEM:ITEMMENU:RAW.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:DISPLAY	Will return a string containing a list of semi-colon-separated category names assigned to the version of the node. Any category containing mandatory attributes will be suffixed with an exclamation in square brackets - [!].
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:MAND	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether a category containing a mandatory attribute is assigned to the version of the node.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on the presence of the <category> category.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:DISPLAY	Will return a string containing a list of semi-colon-separated attribute values for the category specified in <category>. If either attribute sets or multi-value attributes are contained in the category they will be displayed in the following syntax:
'attval1;attval2;[SET3:attval4,attval5,[MV6:attval7,attval8]];attval9'
Here attval1, attval2 & attval9 are regular attribute values. [SET3: represents the start of an attribute set where 3 is the attribute ID of the set (see note). Contained in the attribute set are two regular attributes (attval4 & attval5) and a multi-value attribute, starting [MV6:, with 6 being the attribute ID of the multi-value attribute. The multi-value attribute contains two values for attribute 6, these are: attval7 & attval8.

N.B: Attribute ID's can be identified by looking at the browser status bar whilst hovering over the attribute name in the category definition page.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:ID	Will return the ID of <category> if the category is present.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:<attribute>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a non-blank value in the category, <category>. If an attribute set is specified in <attribute>, a single entry in any one of the set's attribute values will cause this to return TRUE.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, a single entry in any one will also cause this to return TRUE.  <attribute> can also be nested within an attribute set either as a regular attribute or a multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category>. If <attribute> is an attribute set or a multi-value attribute a comma-separated list of values will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:<attribute>:ID	Will return the ID of the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> if it is present. If <attribute> exists inside an attribute set, it will be returned if no attribute matching <attribute> exists at the top level in the category.  If <attribute> exists at the top level of the category and within an attribute set of the same category, the attribute ID at the top level (not within the set) will take precedence.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a value equal to <attval> in the category, <category>.  <attribute> may be an attribute within an attribute set (including a multi-value), or any element within a multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT
Will return the number of multi-value attributes in use.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>
Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of a specific non-blank element in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.  If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:<attval>
Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of <attval> in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>,  for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> at the index location <n> where <n> is a positive integer between 1 and n.  The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.  For example, if <attval> exists in the third element of <attribute>, the number 3 will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>	Uses the SET operator allowing attribute sets to be explicitly referenced.  This example will return TRUE if attribute, <attribute> within set, <set> is non-blank.  Only attributes within <set> can be referenced so if <attribute> exists outside the set, it will not be found.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, TRUE will be returned if any field within it is non-blank.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the attribute, <attribute>, for the category, <category>, if <attribute> is an attribute within <set>.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, a comma-separated list of the defined values will be returned.  If no defined value exists, either in a multi-value attribute, or a standard attribute, an empty list will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:ID	Will return the ID of the attribute <attribute> within the set <set>.  If <attribute> exists outside <set> it will not be returned.  <attribute> can be either a regular or multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE depending on whether an attribute, <attribute>, exists with a value equal to <attval> in the set, <set>.  If <attribute> is a multi-value attribute, all elements will be checked for equality against <attval>, if any match, TRUE will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT	Will return number of multi-value attributes that have been populated.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>	Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of a specific non-blank element in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:<attval>	Will return TRUE/FALSE for the presence of <attval> in a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n>. The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:<n>:DISPLAY	Will return the value in the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> at the index location <n> where <n> is a positive integer between 1 and n.  The value of <n> must be a positive integer between 1 and n where n does not exceed the length of the multi-value attribute.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:SET:<set>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a set, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, has a non-blank attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>. If n exceeds the length of the multi-value attribute, an empty string will be returned.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:DISPLAY	Will display the value of an attribute <attribute> within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:ID	Will display the ID of an attribute <attribute> within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:<attribute>:<attval>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, has a attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <n>, within the category, <category> that is equal to the value specified in <attval>.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:COUNT	Returns the number of multi-value attributes in use in the multi-value set.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:<m>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, at index location <n> has a multi-value attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <m>, that is non-blank.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:<m>:DISPLAY	Will display the value of an multi-value attribute <attribute>, at the index location <m>, within a multi-value set, <set> at the index location <n>, within the category, <category>.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:<m>:<attval>	Will return TRUE or FALSE where the multi-value set, <set>, at the index location <n>, has a multi-value-attribute, <attribute>, at the index location <m> whose value is equal to the value specified in <attval>.
VERSIONCAT:<vernum>:<category>:MVSET:<set>:<n>:MV:<attribute>:INDEX:<attval>	Will return the first index of the multi-value attribute, <attribute>, within a multi-value set, for the category, <category> where <attval> is equal to the value contained in the multi-value attribute at index.
The VERSIONCAT sub-tag is essentially the same as the CAT sub-tag, but returns data for a specific version of a node whereas the CAT sub-tag returns data for the latest version of a node. A detailed example of the CAT sub-tag and several other methods of Categories and Attributes reporting can be found here.

See also: CAT   LLURL   TOJSON   

		
WFACTION:<operation>
This sub-tag offers powerful capabilities to manipulate workflows in large volumes at the server. Users are only able to manipulate workflows with the same level of permissions as through the regular user interface.

Expects the SubWorkID of a Workflow instance in the main tag.

Action	Description
WFACTION:ARCHIVE	Changes the status of a Stopped or Completed workflow to Archived.
WFACTION:DELETE	Deletes a Stopped or Completed workflow
WFACTION:RESUME	Changes the status of a Suspended workflow to Executing.
WFACTION:STOP	Changes the status of an Executing or Suspended workflow to Stopped.

Please note that WFACTION:STOP cannot stop a workflow if it is being run in a WebReport Step that is executed by the Workflow agent.
WFACTION:SUSPEND	Changes the status of an Executing workflow to Suspended.
WFACTION:SETATTR:<attname>:<value>	Sets the value of the named workflow attribute.

For example, [LL_REPTAG='123456' WFACTION:SETATTR:FIRSTNAME:Bob /] will populate an attribute called FIRSTNAME with the value 'Bob' in the workflow instance with SubWorkID 123456.
WFACTION:SETATTR:MV:<attname>:<value>	Sets the value of the named workflow multi-value attribute.

For example, [LL_REPTAG='123456' WFACTION:SETATTR:MV:NATIONALITY:British /] will populate a multi-value attribute called NATIONALITY with the value 'British' in the workflow instance with SubWorkID 123456.
WFACTION:SETATTR:MV:<attname>:<n>:<value>	Sets the value of the nth field of the named workflow multi-value attribute.

For example, [LL_REPTAG='123456' WFACTION:SETATTR:MV:NATIONALITY:2:Irish /] will populate the second field of a multi-value attribute called NATIONALITY with the value 'Irish' in the workflow instance with SubWorkID 123456.
WFACTION:SETATTR:MV++:<attname>:<value>	Adds a field to the named workflow multi-value attribute, and sets its value.

For example, [LL_REPTAG='123456' WFACTION:SETATTR:MV++:NATIONALITY:Canadian /] will add a field to a multi-value attribute called NATIONALITY, and populate it with the value 'Canadian' in the workflow instance with SubWorkID 123456.
If the multi-value attribute already contained fields populated with 'British' and 'Irish', then 'Canadian' would be added as the third field.
Example: [LL_REPTAG=WORKID WFACTION:SUSPEND /] changes the status of an Executing workflow, identified by the WORKID column returned from the data source, to Suspended.

See also: NODEACTION   USERACTION   SETWFATTR   

		
