WFTASKACTION:<format>
This sub-tag will update data for workflow steps that are awaiting completion.

The main tag must contain a list containing the workflow task's workid, subworkid and taskid, e.g. [LL_REPTAG_{ workid, subworkid, taskid } /].

Format	Description
WFTASKACTION:REASSIGN:<user or group>	Will reassign the workflow step to the user or group specified in the main tag. Acceptable arguments are the user ID, user login name or group ID.
For example: [LL_REPTAG_{98765,98765,3} WFTASKACTION:REASSIGN:1234 /] will reassign the step with workID = 98765, subworkID = 98765 and taskID = 3 to the user or group with ID 1234.
WFTASKACTION:SENDON
or
WFTASKACTION:SENDON:<disposition>	Will send on the workflow step.
If the step has multiple dispositions, pass in the disposition value as an optional argument.
If no disposition value is provided, then the step will be sent on with the default value that the workflow step expects.
Note that workflow step dispositions are case-sensitive, so if a disposition value is provided in the tag, it must exactly match a disposition expected by the workflow step.
This option will only work from a standalone WebReport, and won't work if run from a WebReport called from a WR Trigger defined in a Workflow.

Examples:

[LL_REPTAG_{98765,98765,3} WFTASKACTION:SENDON /] will send on the step with workID = 98765, subworkID = 98765 and taskID = 3.

[LL_REPTAG_{98765,98765,4} WFTASKACTION:SENDON:Reject /] will send on the step with workID = 98765, subworkID = 98765 and taskID = 4 with the disposition value "Reject".
WFTASKACTION is one of a handful of specialized sub-tags that are called Action Sub-tags. Additional information on using this and other action sub-tags, can be found in the Advanced Information section: Action Sub-tags.

		
