WKSPACTION:<operation>
The WKSPACTION sub-tag offers actions for business workspaces. These actions and operations are very powerful and thus should be used carefully. The sub-tag itself behaves like other WebReport sub-tags. This implies that users, who are not allowed to perform an action using the regular user interface, can also not run the WKSPACTION operation.

Action	Operation	Description
RELATION	ADD:<relation type>:<single workspace ID or list of workspace IDs>	Adds the child or parent business relationships to the current business workspace.

For example, WKSPACTION:RELATION:ADD:CHILD:{34567,54323} adds the related child business relationships with ID 34567 and ID 54323 to the current business workspace.

Valid values for the <relation type> parameter are CHILD or PARENT.
REMOVE:<relation type>:<single workspace ID or list of workspace IDs>	Removes the child or parent business relationships from the current business workspace.

For example, WKSPACTION:RELATION:REMOVE:CHILD:34567 Removes the related child business relationship with ID 34567 from the current business workspace.

Valid values for the <relation type> parameter are CHILD or PARENT.
BOREF	UPDATE:<extSysID>:<boType>:<boID>
UPDATE:<boTypeID>:<boID>
UPDATE:<param assoc>
Sets or changes the business object reference of a business workspace.

The BOREF actions take a business object identifier which can either be specified as [external system ID, business object type, business object ID] or as [business object type ID, business object ID]. The values can be either passed individually or as an ASSOC with these keys:

Key	Parameter	Data type
"EXTSYSID"	External system ID	String
"BOTYPE"	Business object type	String
"BOID"	Business object ID	String
"BOTYPEID"	Business object type ID	Integer
Examples:

1. Specify business object with external system ID, business object type and business object ID

[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:"F7K":"Contract":"00012345679" /]
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:[LL_REPTAG=EXTSYSID /]:[LL_REPTAG=BOTYPE /]:[LL_REPTAG=BOID /] /]
2. Specify business object with business object type ID and business object ID

[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:32:"00012345679" /]
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:[LL_REPTAG=BOTYPEID /]:[LL_REPTAG=BOID /] /]
3. Use ASSOC to pass business object identifier values

[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "EXTSYSID", "[LL_REPTAG=EXTSYSID /]" },
    { "BOTYPE"  , "[LL_REPTAG=BOTYPE /]"   },
    { "BOID"    , "[LL_REPTAG=BOID /]"     }
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:BoRef /]
                
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:[LL_REPTAG_!BoRef /] /]

[LL_REPTAG_'{
    { "BOTYPEID", [LL_REPTAG_&bo_type_id /] },
    { "BOID"    , "[LL_REPTAG_&bo_id /]"    }
}' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:BoRef /]
                
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:UPDATE:[LL_REPTAG_!BoRef /] /]
Note that the values for keys EXTSYSID, BOTYPE and BOID need to form a string literal, therefore they need to be put in quotation marks!

REMOVE:<extSysID>:<boType>:<boID>
REMOVE:<boTypeID>:<boID>
REMOVE:<param assoc>
Removes the business object reference of a business workspace.

The usage patterns are identical to those for action UPDATE. See the examples there and replace UPDATE with REMOVE. For example:
[LL_REPTAG=DATAID WKSPACTION:BOREF:REMOVE:"F7K":"Contract":"00012345679" /]
		
WKSPINFO:<operation>
The WKSPINFO sub-tag returns information about the current workspace according to the operation parameter that has been provided.

Action	Operation	Description
RELATION	WKSPINFO:RELATION	The related child business workspaces for the current workspace.
WKSPINFO:RELATION:<relation type>	Returns the related business workspaces filtered by the relation type for the current workspace.

For example, WKSPINFO:RELATION:CHILD returns the related child business workspaces for the current workspace.

