XENGADNACTION
This sub-tag provides capabilities to perform ADN actions related to XENGADN.

Syntax	Description
XENGADNACTION:GENERATE	Generates not allocated (Status = 0) ADN Numbers in Bulk.

Example : [LL_REPTAG_'' XENGADNACTION:GENERATE:[LL_REPTAG_&ADNCategoryID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&ADNReferenceAttributeID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Quantity /]:[LL_REPTAG_!DependentAttributes /] /]

NOTE: Value of quantity should be less than 1000.
Dependent Attributes is an Assoc with key in CATID_ATTRID format and value as the value of respective attribute. Consider values of normal attributes only and only the first value of the attribute, ignore all the other values.
There is no explicit validation done on dependent attributes. User has to give valid values for dependent attributes.

Example to create dependent attributes in assoc format:

[LL_REPTAG_&AttributeValue1 SETVAR:AttrValue1 /]

[LL_REPTAG_'CatID_AttrID' SETVAR:CatAttrIDs /]

[LL_REPTAG_'' ASSOCACTION:CREATE SETVAR:DependentAttributes /]

[LL_REPTAG_!DependentAttributes ASSOCACTION:ADD:[LL_REPTAG_!CatAttrIDs /]:[LL_REPTAG_!AttrValue1 /] SETVAR:DependentAttributes /]

Pass the DependentAttributes in assoc format to the subtag as a parameter by using [LL_REPTAG_!DependentAttributes /] tag

XENGADNACTION:LOCK	Used to lock ADN Number
ADNID can be of status 'Not Allocated' or 'Referenced'. For any other status, sub tag will return an error.
The input ADN ID of status 'Not Allocated' and 'Referenced' will be locked and moved to status 'Locked unallocated' and 'Locked referenced' respectively.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&ADNID XENGADNACTION:LOCK /]
XENGADNACTION:UNLOCK	Used to unlock ADN Number
ADNID can be of status 'Locked unallocated' or 'Locked referenced'. For any other status, sub tag will return an error.
The input ADN ID of status 'Locked unallocated' and 'Locked referenced' will be unlocked and moved to status 'Not Allocated' and 'Referenced' respectively.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&ADNID XENGADNACTION:UNLOCK /]
XENGADNACTION:DELETE	Used to delete ADN Number which are in 'Not Allocated' status.

Error is returned, if ADNID is not in status 'Not Allocated (0)'.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&ADNID XENGADNACTION:DELETE /]
XENGADNACTION:DEREFER	Used to derefer an ADN Number from a node
Error is returned, if ADNID is not in status 'Referenced (1)'.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&NODEID XENGADNACTION:DEREFER:[LL_REPTAG_&ADNID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&AllVersions /] /]

NOTE: The node will be renamed to its original name if there are no multiple references.

When AllVersion is set to TRUE, each version of the node is derefered and renamed to its original name if there are no multiple references

If the ADN Reference attribute is mandatory on the associated category then DEREFER action will not be allowed.
ADN Number value on the category attribute associated to the object will be cleared.
XENGADNACTION:REFER	Used to refer an ADN Number to a node
Error is returned, if ADNID is not in status 'Not allocated(0)' or 'Referenced (1)'.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&NODEID XENGADNACTION:REFER:[LL_REPTAG_&CATID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&ATTRID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&ADNNumber /] /]

NOTE: If the existing ADN Number is not refered to any node then it will be put into Not allocated status
		
