XENGCRTACTION
This sub-tag provides capabilities to perform revision actions related to XENGCRT.

Syntax	Description
XENGCRTACTION:CONTROL	Convert a document into a controlled document from Master Workspace and Project Workspace.

If the document is present in Master Workspace:
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:CONTROL /]

If the document is present in Project Workspace:
RevisionStatusID - ID of Revision Status.
MasterWorkspaceID - ID of Master Workspace.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:CONTROL:[LL_REPTAG_&RevisionStatusID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&MasterWorkspaceID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:SIGNOUT	Perform revision signout of a controlled document.
RevisionStatusID - ID of Revision Status.
ProjectID - ID of Project.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:SIGNOUT:[LL_REPTAG_&RevisionStatusID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&ProjectID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:CHANGESTATUS	Change revision status of a controlled document.
RevisionStatusID - ID of Revision Status.
ProjectID - ID of Project.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:CHANGESTATUS:[LL_REPTAG_&RevisionStatusID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&ProjectID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:SIGNIN	Perform revision signin of a controlled document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:SIGNIN:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:REVISIONCANCEL	Perform revision cancel of a controlled document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:REVISIONCANCEL:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:MARKOBSOLETE	To mark controlled document as obsolete.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:MARKOBSOLETE:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGCRTACTION:DECONTROL	Decontrol a controlled document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:DECONTROL /]
XENGCRTACTION:DECONTROLANDDELETE	Decontrol and delete a controlled document and its revisions. Unreserves ADN number associated to the document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:DECONTROLANDDELETE /]
XENGCRTACTION:REVISIONS	Fetch the revision history information of a controlled document
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGCRTACTION:REVISIONS /]
		
XENGCRTControlDocumentCount
This sub-tag will return a RecArray with records of the control documents based on user-selected revision statuses and revision indicators.
Revision_Statuses is used to pass multiple revision statuses, where revision statuses must be comma separated.
Revision_Indicators is used to pass multiple revision indicators, where revision indicators must be comma separated.
Example: [LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID XENGCRTControlDocumentCount:[LL_REPTAG_WIDGETCONTAINERID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Revision_Statuses /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Revision_Indicators /] SETVAR:data /]

Values for Revision Status which will be passed as parameter values must be specified in the Revision Control configuration.
List of valid values for Revision Indicators are: Archive, Cancel, ControlledSignedOut, Current, Decontrol, Initial, Obsolete, SignedOut, SignedOutArchived.

This subtag will return data only in cases of valid inputs and for error scenarios, no results will be displayed.

		
XENGSFM
This sub-tag provides capabilities to get the State Flows releated information.

Syntax	Description
XENGSFM:STATEFLOWSFORASSOCIATION	Retrieves the applicable State Flows information of the document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFM:STATEFLOWSFORASSOCIATION /]
XENGSFM:STATEFLOWINFO	Displays the details of the state flow associated with the document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFM:STATEFLOWINFO /]
XENGSFM:MYAPPROVERLIST	Retrieves the list of Current State Roles/Groups in which the specified user is part of for a given document. Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFM:MYAPPROVERLIST:[LL_REPTAG_&UserID /] /]
XENGSFM:APPLICABLETRANSITIONS	Displays the transitions to which the document can be transitioned from its current state.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFM:APPLICABLETRANSITIONS /]
XENGSFM:STATEFLOWDOCUMENTS	Retrieves the list of documents from the specified workspace on which the specified user has atleast watch permissions. Example : [LL_REPTAG_'[LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID /]' XENGSFM:STATEFLOWDOCUMENTS:[LL_REPTAG_&workspaceid /] /]
XENGSFM:STATEFLOWREPORT	
This sub-tag will return a RecArray with records of the documents associated to Stateflows and its status based on user-selected workspace and stateflow.
Stateflow is used to fetch the documents associated with the particular Stateflow from the source workspace and in case of multiple Stateflow, pass with comma separated.
WIDGETCONTAINERID is used to pass the source workspace ID.
Example: [LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID XENGSFM:STATEFLOWREPORT:[LL_REPTAG_WIDGETCONTAINERID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Stateflow /] SETVAR:data /]


This subtag will return data only in cases of valid inputs and for error scenarios, no results will be displayed.

		
XENGSFMACTION
This sub-tag provides capabilities to perform State flow actions on Documents related to State flows.

Syntax	Description
XENGSFMACTION:ASSOCIATE	Associates the document to a stateflow
STATEFLOWID - ID of State flow to be associated.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:ASSOCIATE:[LL_REPTAG_&STATEFLOWID /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:TRANSITION	Performs the transition on the document with given transition and roles.
STATEFLOWID - ID of State flow.
TRANSITIONID - ID of Transition.
PERFORMERIDs - List of PerformerIDs
Comments - Transition Comments
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:TRANSITION:[LL_REPTAG_&STATEFLOWID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&TRANSITIONID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&PERFORMERIDs /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Comments /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:ADDASSIGNEE	Adds the given assignee to the state flow associated document.
PERFORMERIDs - List of performers to be added.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:ADDASSIGNEE:[LL_REPTAG_&PERFORMERIDs /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:REMOVEASSIGNEE	Removes assignee from the state flow associated document.
PERFORMERIDs - List of performers to be removed.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:REMOVEASSIGNEE:[LL_REPTAG_&PERFORMERIDs /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:DELEGATE	Delegated the assignment from the logged in user to the given user.
PERFORMERID - ID of Performer to be delegated to.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:DELEGATE:[LL_REPTAG_&PERFORMERID /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:CLAIM	Claims the given document on behalf of given roles.
PERFORMERID - List of Performer IDs to be claimed on behalf of.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:CLAIM:[LL_REPTAG_&PERFORMERIDs /] /]
XENGSFMACTION:DISASSOCIATE	Disassociates the document from the stateflow.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:DISASSOCIATE /]
XENGSFMACTION:CHANGEPLANNEDENDDATE	Edits and assigns new planned end date on a stateflow assigned document.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGSFMACTION:CHANGEPLANNEDENDDATE:[LL_REPTAG_&NEWPLANNEDENDDATE /] /]
		
XENGTMACTION
This sub-tag provides capabilities to perform Tag functionality

Syntax	Description
XENGTMACTION:ASSOCIATETAG	Associates Tag to a document
Example: [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGTMACTION:ASSOCIATETAG:[LL_REPTAG_&TAGID /] /]
XENGTMACTION:DISASSOCIATETAG	Disassociates Tag from a document
Example: [LL_REPTAG_&DocumentID XENGTMACTION:DISASSOCIATETAG:[LL_REPTAG_&TAGID /] /]
XENGTMACTION:DEACTIVATE	Deactivates a Tag. fails if there are documents associated with the Tag
Example: [LL_REPTAG_&TagID XENGTMACTION:DEACTIVATE /]
		
XENGTMDocuments
This sub-tag will return a RecArray with records of the Tag data and associated documents for which the specified user has read permissions.

Example: [LL_REPTAG_&ACTUALUSERID XENGTMDocuments:[LL_REPTAG_&WIDGETCONTAINERID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&TAGID /] SETVAR:data /]
ACTUALUSERID is the user id for whom this report is required for
WIDGETCONTAINERID is optional. it is used to filter and return only the records of documents that belong to this Workspace
TAGID is optional. it is used to filter and return only the records of documents that are associated to this Tag

This subtag will return data only in cases of valid inputs and for error scenarios, no results will be displayed.

		
XENGTRANSMITTAL
This sub-tag provides capabilities to get details related to Transmittal Workspace.

Syntax	Description
XENGTRANSMITTAL:TRANSMITTALINFO	Used to get details related to Transmittal Workspace.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTAL:TRANSMITTALINFO /]
XENGTRANSMITTAL:TRANSMITTALREPORT	
This sub-tag will return a RecArray with records of the transmittals based on user-selected status and workspace.
Status is used to return all the transmittals in that particular status from the source workspace and in case of multiple status , pass with comma separated.
WIDGETCONTAINERID is used to pass the source workspace ID.
Example: [LL_REPTAG_ACTUALUSERID XENGTRANSMITTAL:TRANSMITTALREPORT:[LL_REPTAG_WIDGETCONTAINERID /]:[LL_REPTAG_&Status /] SETVAR:data /]


This subtag will return data only in cases of valid inputs and for error scenarios, no results will be displayed.

		
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION
This sub-tag provides capabilities to perform actions related to XENGTRANSMITTAL.

Syntax	Description
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:ADDRECIPIENTS	Used to add recipients to Transmittal Workspace.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:ADDRECIPIENTS:[LL_REPTAG_&RecipientIDList /]:[LL_REPTAG_&DeliveryMethod /] /]
RecipientIDList - List of User/group IDs
DeliveryMethod - ID of the delivery method type. Below are the allowed values
1 - Email Coversheet
2 - Core share
3 - Supplier Exchange
Note: Append the underscore( _ ) at the end of RecipientID for external User
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:PACKAGE	Used to package the Transmittal Workspace.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:PACKAGE /]
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:SEND	Used to Send the Tranmsittal.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:SEND /]

Note: To Send a transmittal with Core delivery method using sub tag, the user who executes the WebReport should have an active core session. User should initiate Core Share action from Smart UI and login to create an active session.
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:VALIDATE	Used to validate the inbound updates of the Transmittal via loadsheet.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:VALIDATE /]
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:PROCESS	Used to process the inboud updates of the Transmittal.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:PROCESS /]
XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:ADDDOCUMENTS	Used to Add documents to Transmittal Workspace.
Example : [LL_REPTAG_&TransmittalID XENGTRANSMITTALACTION:ADDDOCUMENTS:[LL_REPTAG_&DocumentIDList /] /]
		
XLATE
Returns a localised string corresponding to the value in the main tag.

For example, [LL_REPTAG_'WEB_NODECMD.Copy' XLATE /] will return the value of the [WEB_NODECMD.Copy] string from the properties file for the user's environment.